1
00:00:31,280 --> 00:00:33,510
<i>(commentator)</i>
Apollo is saying "Come on!"

2
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:37,519
Apollo is going right. He's going
for another right... another right.

3
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:40,836
Now he's gone for the left.

4
00:00:41,680 --> 00:00:45,798
Down on one knee.
Lou Filippo in there wiping off the glove.

5
00:00:50,640 --> 00:00:52,915
Hard left and a right combination.

6
00:00:53,040 --> 00:00:56,715
<i>(commentator #2)</i> What is keeping him
up, Bill? I don't know.

7
00:00:58,080 --> 00:01:01,436
He can't even get his gloves up
to protect himself.

8
00:01:08,080 --> 00:01:09,991
Down! Stay down!

9
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:13,795
Apollo dancing around
with his arms in the air.

10
00:01:22,760 --> 00:01:24,716
Five...

11
00:01:25,360 --> 00:01:27,920
...six... seven...

12
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:30,235
...eight... nine...

13
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:42,274
<i>(commentator)</i> Apollo can't believe it.

14
00:01:57,920 --> 00:02:01,390
The champion got a left
to the ribs - his right ribs.

15
00:02:08,720 --> 00:02:11,314
- You OK, champ?
- Yeah, I'm OK. I'm OK.

16
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:13,715
- Your rib's broken.
- He broke my ribs.

17
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:16,991
I can't see nothing.
Gotta open my eye. Cut me, Mick.

18
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:19,588
- I don't wanna do it!
- Go on, cut me.

19
00:02:19,720 --> 00:02:22,712
- Cut me.
- OK. Try it. Cut it.

20
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:25,274
You're bleedin' inside.
I'm gonna stop the fight.

21
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:28,437
You ain't stoppin' nothin', man.

22
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:32,350
- You stop this fight, I'll kill you!
- All right. I won't stop it.

23
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:33,959
- I'm goin'!
- You wanna go...

24
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:36,958
- Last round.
- You gotta do it! You gotta get it off!

25
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:39,116
Get it off!

26
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:48,074
<i>(commentator)</i> There's the bell
for the 15th and final round.

27
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:55,518
You better start fightin'. You been
doin' nothin'. You been doin' nothin'.

28
00:02:55,640 --> 00:02:59,758
They look like they've been in a war,
these two.

29
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:08,990
The champion really tagged him.

30
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:12,590
Apollo clearly protecting his right side -
his ribs.

31
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:16,675
- Oh, look at that!
- Body punches!

32
00:03:17,760 --> 00:03:20,672
- Hard left and right.
- See the blood coming out of his mouth.

33
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:23,155
He's spitting out blood now.

34
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:28,676
A tremendous right hand from Rocky.

35
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,756
Go for it. Go for it, Rock!

36
00:03:30,880 --> 00:03:33,348
Listen to this crowd! Left to the ribs.

37
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:36,870
Another to the ribs.
That left hand again. Right to the chin!

38
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:41,596
He's got him up against the ropes!
Apollo, the champion...

39
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:47,111
<i>(Apollo)</i> Ain't gonna be no rematch.
Ain't gonna be no rematch.

40
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:49,595
<i>(Rocky)</i> Don't want one!

41
00:03:59,320 --> 00:04:02,153
- You went 15 rounds. How do you feel?
- All right.

42
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:06,432
What were you thinking about
when that buzzer sounded off?

43
00:04:06,560 --> 00:04:08,073
Adrian!

44
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:09,952
Rocky...

45
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:12,036
Rocky!

46
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:15,596
Rocky!

47
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,069
Rocky!

48
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:21,432
We have had the privilege
of witnessing the greatest exhibition...

49
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:25,269
...of guts and stamina
in the history of the ring.

50
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:27,709
Adrian!

51
00:04:28,280 --> 00:04:29,918
Rocky!

52
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:34,192
Ladies and gentlemen,
we have a split decision.

53
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:39,068
Adrian!

54
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:41,755
Eight for Apollo Creed!

55
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:48,832
- Those fans out there deserve a rematch.
- Ain't gonna be no rematch. Come on!

56
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:52,396
I had enough things
in my face today! Adrian!

57
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:55,956
Rocko! That's my friend. Rocko!

58
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:58,275
You're breaking my jacket.

59
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,719
Paulie!

60
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:02,195
- Adrian! Adrian!
- Rocky!

61
00:05:02,320 --> 00:05:04,470
Adrian! Hey, where's your hat?

62
00:05:04,760 --> 00:05:07,354
- I love you!
- I love <i>you.</i>

63
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:10,636
I love you!

64
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:12,798
I love you!

65
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:15,156
I love you!

66
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,877
Rocky Balboa!

67
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:28,711
Get 'em outta here! Let him breathe,
will ya? Give him air.

68
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:31,308
Sit down, Rocky. Sit down.

69
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:33,510
- Did you think you had it won?
- I don't know.

70
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:38,031
- How about a statement, Rocky?
- I don't know. I'm at a loss for words.

71
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:42,312
- Get back there!
- Rocky, did you think you had it won?

72
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:45,552
- Where's the doctor?
- How's my nose? As bad as Mickey's?

73
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:49,031
It ain't that horrible.
Now give him a break. Get outta there.

74
00:07:49,160 --> 00:07:53,119
- Is that the worst beating you ever took?
- You'll get worse if you don't get out.

75
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:55,390
What did you think in the last round?

76
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:58,080
That I shoulda stayed
at school or somethin'.

77
00:07:58,200 --> 00:08:00,919
- Do you think you have brain damage?
- I don't see any.

78
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:04,828
- <i>(Apollo)</i> Where is he?
- Apollo, how about a statement?

79
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:06,996
Get away from me!

80
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:11,113
Stallion! Stallion!
You got a dull skull, Stallion.

81
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:13,800
You're lucky, so lucky.
What you did was a miracle.

82
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:16,593
You're the luckiest man
on the face of the earth.

83
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:19,632
- Do I look lucky?
- Nobody goes the distance with me.

84
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:22,228
Get up out of that chair,
and finish this fight.

85
00:08:22,360 --> 00:08:24,828
- Don't, please. Sit down.
- Is he serious?

86
00:08:24,960 --> 00:08:28,316
- Did the bell save you, Apollo?
- Bell nothin'. I can beat that chump.

87
00:08:28,440 --> 00:08:31,193
- I'll fight him any place, any time.
- You mean a rematch?

88
00:08:31,320 --> 00:08:33,675
I said any place, any time, man.
Can you hear?

89
00:08:33,800 --> 00:08:36,360
You said there weren't
gonna be no rematch.

90
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:40,268
- Look, chump, any place, any time.
- A rematch could be worth millions.

91
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:44,552
- Well, I'm officially retired now.
- Don't you run out on me now, Stallion.

92
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:47,558
I gave you a shot the first time.
Now I'll give you a second.

93
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:50,513
He sure has a lot of energy.
You got nothin' to prove.

94
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:54,599
I don't care what the hell them judges
said - this is the man that won the fight!

95
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:58,508
I'm gonna show you how lucky you are!
You're gonna fight me again, chump!

96
00:08:58,640 --> 00:09:00,835
Don't run out on me! Come back here!

97
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:03,190
Adrian? You better go home...

98
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:06,198
...cos I'm gonna be busy healin'
here for a while, you know.

99
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:09,471
- I wanna be here.
- Maybe you better go home with Paulie...

100
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:13,388
...and get some - wait a minute -
get some sleep, you know?

101
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:17,954
- I love you.
- I love you.

102
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:20,435
See you later. See you, Mick.

103
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:28,509
<i>(slurred)</i> Can you fix my nose?
I'm a little depressed about my nose.

104
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:33,111
We'll fix that all right.
It's the eye that concerns me.

105
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:35,196
The eye's great.

106
00:09:36,160 --> 00:09:39,118
I ain't never really felt this good.

107
00:09:40,760 --> 00:09:44,355
You guys shoulda seen us tonight.

108
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:46,436
We did good.

109
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:49,356
<i>(mumbles)</i>

110
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:56,554
You had him in the 10th,
and in the 15th he was gone.

111
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:59,956
- You think so?
- Trust me. I was there.

112
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:03,675
- How's your face, Rock?
- I don't know. How's it look?

113
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:06,635
Well, <i>I</i> wouldn't want it.

114
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:10,870
Rocky, I got a little favour
I'd like to ask you.

115
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:14,993
You know your friend Gazzo,
he admires you a lot.

116
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:18,556
- Tell him to give me your old job.
- You mean collectin'?

117
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:20,636
- I'm good with numbers.
- Yeah.

118
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:24,870
OK. As soon as I get finished,
you know, healin' here...

119
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:28,915
...l'll tell him to give you my old job, OK?

120
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:32,271
- I'd appreciate that.
- What are you doing here?

121
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:36,474
Visiting hours are over.
I have to ask you to leave.

122
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:39,676
- Now.
- OK. See you later, Paulie.

123
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:43,193
- OK. Everybody's proud of you, Rock.
- Yeah?

124
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:44,753
- Yeah!
- <i>(nurse)</i> Now.

125
00:10:44,880 --> 00:10:47,348
- I feel good tonight.
- Yeah, you look good.

126
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,835
- Let's go.
- <i>(Paulie whistles)</i>

127
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:55,230
- How are we feeling tonight?
- Oh, very handsome.

128
00:11:03,680 --> 00:11:07,958
- That tastes good.
- My kid would die for your autograph.

129
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:10,116
- Sure.
- Would you sign it to:

130
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:12,993
"My good friend Charlie Flynn."

131
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:16,519
- My hands are so sore.
- It's OK.

132
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:23,111
- It's my first autograph.
- Thank you.

133
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:25,196
You're welcome.

134
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:33,669
To my good friend Charlie Flynn,
who I don't even know.

135
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:43,316
Yo, Apollo?

136
00:11:44,160 --> 00:11:47,197
- Who is it?
- It's just me, Rocky. Listen...

137
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:51,677
- Could you answer me one question?
- Yeah, sure.

138
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:54,155
Did you give me your best?

139
00:11:56,160 --> 00:11:58,594
Yeah. Yeah.

140
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:02,916
Thank you.

141
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:15,313
This year...

142
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:17,396
- You all right?
- Great bein' outside.

143
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:21,069
This coming year you're gonna
make $300,000. This fiscal year.

144
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:23,714
- Hey, Rock!
- How you doin', Pete?

145
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:26,354
- Hey, could you sign my head?
- Yeah, sure.

146
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:29,199
- Thanks.
- Hope it don't go to your brain.

147
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:31,038
- Bet that's heavy.
- A bit.

148
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:33,720
Just think how fast you'll be
when you get it off.

149
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:36,593
Just a minute. Can I borrow this?
Let me use your head.

150
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:40,474
- Sign, Rocky. Sign the deal.
- I wanna talk to you a little bit about this.

151
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:43,751
- It's a standard deal.
- Just for talkin' about shavin' stuff?

152
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:47,555
- Sledgehammers... Whatever. Batteries...
- All kinds of commercials.

153
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:50,353
- Balls and baseballs?
- You're gonna make $300,000.

154
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:53,278
Strike while the iron's hot.
20 minutes, it's all over.

155
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:56,631
- Yeah, people kinda forget.
- The time is now to make a dollar.

156
00:12:56,760 --> 00:13:00,150
Sign it here. It takes you two seconds
to sign. It's a standard deal.

157
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:02,794
OK, I'll sign it,
but I gotta go somewhere now.

158
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:05,514
Where you goin'?
What could be more important?

159
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:08,632
I just gotta do some things,
but I'll be back. I'll talk to you.

160
00:13:08,760 --> 00:13:11,320
- Give me a call, then.
- Where will we call you?

161
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:13,396
- I'll give you a call.
- You got a number?

162
00:13:13,520 --> 00:13:16,796
I'll just call you.
I'll go "Hey! Yo!" I'll call you.

163
00:13:16,920 --> 00:13:18,990
All right, you call.

164
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:21,315
The guy's got brain damage.

165
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:26,712
It's great bein' outta the hospital
and not havin' to take all those pills.

166
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:30,389
And my legs were gettin' so sore
and all that from just layin' there.

167
00:13:30,520 --> 00:13:35,389
I was kind of shrinkin' and all that.
It's great to be outside, you know?

168
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:41,750
- What are we doin' here at the zoo?
- Well, you know, I kinda like the zoo a lot.

169
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:47,034
It's a special place, especially when it
snows - it smells clean and everything.

170
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:49,151
Don't you like the zoo? Huh?

171
00:13:49,280 --> 00:13:52,113
- I like the zoo.
- Yeah, me too.

172
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:57,394
You know, I was wonderin', like...

173
00:13:58,240 --> 00:14:02,631
What do you think you're doin' for,
like, the next, uh... 40 or 50 years?

174
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:05,115
What do you mean?

175
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:14,349
I was wonderin' if, uh... you wouldn't
mind marrying me very much.

176
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:18,035
What'd ya say?

177
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:22,152
If you wouldn't mind
marryin' me too much.

178
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,560
Yes. I'd like to marry you.

179
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:30,630
- Yeah?
- Yes.

180
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:33,876
- Yeah?
- Yes.

181
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,556
I'll be a good guy, I promise.

182
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:49,800
I ain't gonna do nothin' wrong. I ain't
gonna leave no hair in the sink or nothin'.

183
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:53,880
Things are gonna be great,
you know that?

184
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:57,392
Hey, we're gettin' married, you know.
You wanna come?

185
00:14:57,520 --> 00:15:00,592
If you can get out for the weekend,
I'll send you an invitation!

186
00:15:00,720 --> 00:15:02,676
That's fantastic, ain't it?

187
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:05,360
<i>(Tarzan-like call)</i>

188
00:15:05,480 --> 00:15:07,710
<i>(bell rings)</i>

189
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:15,756
<i>Rocky Balboa,</i>
<i>volete prendere Adriana Pernino...</i>

190
00:15:15,880 --> 00:15:19,759
<i>...qui presente per la vostra moglie?</i>
- Yeah, absolutely. Yes.

191
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:25,830
<i>Adriana Pernino, volete prendere a Rocky</i>
<i>Balboa qui presente per vostro marito?</i>

192
00:15:25,960 --> 00:15:27,757
- I do.
- Thanks.

193
00:15:27,880 --> 00:15:30,633
<i>Io declaro che siete sposo e sposa.</i>

194
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:36,911
You may kiss the bride now.

195
00:15:37,040 --> 00:15:39,395
- I gotta take this off?
- Yeah.

196
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:51,678
<i>Vada in pace.</i>
Go in peace and God bless you.

197
00:15:51,800 --> 00:15:54,837
Uh, thanks, Father.
You done real good. I'm proud of ya.

198
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:57,838
- Things are gonna be great.
- Rocky, congratulations!

199
00:15:57,960 --> 00:16:00,554
Thanks a lot, thanks a lot. Thanks, Tony.

200
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:04,349
- I ain't gonna need any luck.
- Rock, you wanna buy into the pet shop?

201
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:06,835
Thanks, but I'm gonna
do commercials instead.

202
00:16:06,960 --> 00:16:09,315
- Commercials? What for? Concussion?
- Yeah!

203
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:11,510
- Rocky!
- Yeah.

204
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:13,551
Ain't that father somethin'?

205
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:17,194
- Good luck to the both of ya.
- Thanks, Mick.

206
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:20,153
I gotta go back to the gym.
I got a couple of good prospects.

207
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:22,550
- Are they really good?
- Pretty good.

208
00:16:22,680 --> 00:16:26,116
- See you around. Thanks for coming.
<i>- (Paulie)</i> Can we go drink now?

209
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:28,708
<i>(Gazzo)</i> Can I borrow
the bridegroom for one minute?

210
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:32,389
- You look beautiful, Adrian.
- She really turned out pretty.

211
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:37,674
Listen, how much money you make from
your last fight? How much did you clear?

212
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:39,870
- About 37 grand.
- Taxes kill you.

213
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:43,754
What do you wanna do with
your money now? Put 'em on the street?

214
00:16:43,880 --> 00:16:47,156
- I told you. I just got married here.
- I know, and I'm happy for you.

215
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:50,318
How's about investing
in condominiums? It's safe.

216
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:53,238
- Condominiums?
- Yeah, condominiums.

217
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:57,396
I never use them.

218
00:16:58,560 --> 00:17:01,120
<i>(</i># <i>Beach-Boy-style harmonising)</i>

219
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:30,433
- Hey, yo! What are youse doin'?
- Hey, Rock! What's happenin', man?

220
00:17:30,560 --> 00:17:33,552
Well, you know,
I just got a little married, you know.

221
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:36,148
- Congratulations!
- You guys drinkin' some wine?

222
00:17:36,280 --> 00:17:39,272
- Yeah, we're doin' it.
- Keep singin'. I like that stuff.

223
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:43,791
- Somethin' for him.
- # There are two kinds of love

