You have wasted our time, sir. This is
a complete bust, the whole afternoon.

447
00:32:19,720 --> 00:32:24,475
Leonard. Leonard, where are you going?
I want you to take him with you, Leonard.

448
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:26,875
Take him with you.
He is not a professional.

449
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:31,755
I only work with professionals. You cost
us thousands because you can't read.

450
00:32:32,600 --> 00:32:35,751
"'Lt's no time to cuss me'
snarled the robber."

451
00:32:35,880 --> 00:32:41,273
"'By God, fellas. Grab your rifles and take
colour... cover."' How does that sound?

452
00:32:41,400 --> 00:32:43,072
- It's good.
- Yeah?

453
00:32:43,200 --> 00:32:46,431
Being a good reader's gonna
help me get a good office job.

454
00:32:46,560 --> 00:32:49,233
- Wanna hear some more?
- I can't wait.

455
00:32:50,640 --> 00:32:52,153
OK.

456
00:32:52,280 --> 00:32:56,831
"'There ain't no cover' said Brad Lincoln.
'We better head for the canyon."'

457
00:32:56,960 --> 00:32:59,679
- You read nice.
- Thank you. You lie nice.

458
00:32:59,800 --> 00:33:01,756
Thank you.

459
00:33:03,600 --> 00:33:05,830
How far did you go in high school,
Mr Balboa?

460
00:33:05,960 --> 00:33:08,474
- Uh, ninth.
- And one last question.

461
00:33:08,600 --> 00:33:10,955
Do you have a criminal record?

462
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:14,755
Nothin' worth braggin' about.

463
00:33:17,120 --> 00:33:20,635
Would you be interested in
some sort of manual labour?

464
00:33:20,760 --> 00:33:23,354
Well, I got nothing against
honest manual labour.

465
00:33:23,520 --> 00:33:28,878
It's just that I'd like to see if I could make
a livin' sittin' down, like you're doin'.

466
00:33:29,680 --> 00:33:33,116
Can I be honest? No one's
going to offer you an office job.

467
00:33:33,240 --> 00:33:36,835
There's too much competition.
Why don't you fight?

468
00:33:36,960 --> 00:33:40,316
I've read somewhere
you're a very good fighter.

469
00:33:41,080 --> 00:33:43,036
Yeah. Well...

470
00:33:43,920 --> 00:33:47,117
Was you ever punched in the face
500 times a night?

471
00:33:47,800 --> 00:33:50,155
Stings after a while, you know.

472
00:33:52,120 --> 00:33:54,873
Thank you very much for your time.
I appreciate it.

473
00:34:05,120 --> 00:34:08,795
Mr Balboa, I'm very sorry.
We have nothing.

474
00:34:08,920 --> 00:34:11,559
- Are you sure?
- Next.

475
00:34:11,840 --> 00:34:16,516
Look, pal, you gotta be realistic. You got
no high-school diploma, no qualifications.

476
00:34:16,640 --> 00:34:20,997
Wouldn't you be more content with
a good-paying menial labour job?

477
00:34:22,440 --> 00:34:24,396
Thanks.

478
00:34:25,080 --> 00:34:28,038
The way I see it is I can get
another job if I wanna.

479
00:34:28,160 --> 00:34:31,948
But do I wanna? Do I wanna be doin'
something I ain't gonna be happy doin'?

480
00:34:32,080 --> 00:34:35,277
Plus, you know,
we need the money <i>now,</i> Butkus.

481
00:34:36,200 --> 00:34:38,395
Dogs don't wanna hear <i>my</i> problems.

482
00:34:38,520 --> 00:34:40,556
Come on.

483
00:34:40,680 --> 00:34:45,674
Yeah. I wish I was a canine sometimes.
Gimme a kiss.

484
00:34:45,800 --> 00:34:50,476
- The only job I got's luggin' beef.
- You got nothin' better than haulin' beef?

485
00:34:50,600 --> 00:34:55,310
That's all I got and we're cutting back too.
So, Rocky, it'd be from week to week.

486
00:34:55,440 --> 00:34:58,159
That's OK with me, but when can I start?

487
00:34:58,280 --> 00:35:01,477
- How about tomorrow?
- Well, how about today?

488
00:35:02,640 --> 00:35:06,474
OK. We got a load comin' in.
Hey, Paulie, you look kinda skinny there.

489
00:35:06,600 --> 00:35:10,115
- Yeah, he's losin' weight, ain't he?
- Don't bother to thank me.

490
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:14,836
Hey, thanks a lot, Paulie. You don't
have to thank me for the watch, either.

491
00:36:09,760 --> 00:36:11,716
Quittin' time!

492
00:36:36,560 --> 00:36:39,677
There's the best-lookin' thing
I seen all day.

493
00:36:41,120 --> 00:36:44,795
- You look tired.
- No, no. My face is tired. <i>I</i> feel OK.

494
00:36:44,920 --> 00:36:48,754
- You wanna take a hot bath?
- No, come on. I feel dynamic. Honest.

495
00:36:48,880 --> 00:36:54,318
Hey, listen, tomorrow... I was thinking at
work, maybe after work I'll take you out.

496
00:36:54,440 --> 00:36:57,432
You wanna do somethin' nice, huh?
You wanna do that?

497
00:36:57,560 --> 00:37:00,916
- I'd like to do that. How's your stomach?
- Fine.

498
00:37:01,040 --> 00:37:03,395
You look great. Do you know that?

499
00:37:55,800 --> 00:37:59,793
- Hey, Rock, they just like old friends.
- Old friends never tasted this good.

500
00:37:59,920 --> 00:38:01,876
I heard that.

501
00:38:11,040 --> 00:38:12,473
Yo!

502
00:38:12,600 --> 00:38:14,556
Yo, Rock!

503
00:38:15,880 --> 00:38:17,711
You wanted me, Frank?

504
00:38:17,840 --> 00:38:19,796
I gotta let you go.

505
00:38:22,640 --> 00:38:25,359
How come? I'm workin' hard.
I'm doin' good.

506
00:38:25,480 --> 00:38:29,314
Yeah, but we gotta cut back on manpower
and you ain't got enough time in.

507
00:38:29,440 --> 00:38:31,396
Seniority.

508
00:38:32,880 --> 00:38:35,872
How about if I take a cut in pay, all right?

509
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:38,355
Can't do it. Union rules.

510
00:38:39,600 --> 00:38:41,556
Rules, rules.

511
00:38:45,600 --> 00:38:47,955
- Can I finish out the day?
- Sure.

512
00:38:48,720 --> 00:38:50,676
Hey, Rocky... I'm sorry.

513
00:38:51,760 --> 00:38:53,716
Yeah, me too.

514
00:39:00,080 --> 00:39:03,072
<i>(Paulie)</i> You got more stories
than a book, you know that?

515
00:39:03,200 --> 00:39:07,113
There's my brother-in-law, Rocky.
Gimme the five.

516
00:39:07,240 --> 00:39:09,708
My brother-in-law come to visit me.

517
00:39:09,840 --> 00:39:12,752
How you doin'? How's everything?
How's business? OK?

518
00:39:12,880 --> 00:39:14,393
Yeah.

519
00:39:14,520 --> 00:39:19,310
- Lookin' over your old stompin' ground?
- Yeah. Listen, you wanna buy this car?

520
00:39:19,440 --> 00:39:22,159
- I thought you liked it.
- I don't need it no more.

521
00:39:22,280 --> 00:39:24,589
I can't make these right turns
with my bad eye.

522
00:39:24,720 --> 00:39:27,678
Keep hittin' trash cans
and things like that.

523
00:39:27,800 --> 00:39:30,712
- You got problems? You need bread?
- No, everything's OK.

524
00:39:30,840 --> 00:39:34,230
This car'd look great
wrapped around you, wouldn't it?

525
00:39:34,360 --> 00:39:37,352
Look, you need a hand-out,
I'll give you a hand-out.

526
00:39:37,480 --> 00:39:42,110
No, I don't need no hand-out, Paulie.
Look, you wanna buy the car?

527
00:39:42,240 --> 00:39:45,516
Sure. Why don't you be smart
and fight again?

528
00:39:48,160 --> 00:39:51,311
That's OK. I don't need to fight no more.
You wanna buy the car?

529
00:39:51,440 --> 00:39:53,635
You wanna pick up the payments?

530
00:39:53,760 --> 00:39:57,992
My sister givin' you a hard time?
If she is, you break her teeth.

531
00:39:59,160 --> 00:40:03,790
I appreciate the advice, Paulie,
but I kinda like her teeth where they are.

532
00:40:03,920 --> 00:40:06,957
There you go. You bought yourself a car.

533
00:40:07,720 --> 00:40:11,713
Good car, you know.
Gotta buckle up for safety and all that.

534
00:40:12,840 --> 00:40:15,195
Where you goin'? You need a lift?

535
00:40:16,280 --> 00:40:18,236
Nah.

536
00:40:18,720 --> 00:40:20,676
See you around.

537
00:40:27,800 --> 00:40:30,155
Hey! Say hi to my sister for me!

538
00:40:32,040 --> 00:40:35,237
Hey, listen,
if you two need the car, just ask!

539
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:50,439
When did you get home?
I thought you were at work.

540
00:40:50,560 --> 00:40:53,472
No, I... I ain't at work no more. I got, uh...

541
00:40:54,600 --> 00:40:56,670
I got canned today.

542
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:59,030
Oh.

543
00:40:59,160 --> 00:41:01,549
- What happened?
- I don't know. I was...

544
00:41:02,520 --> 00:41:07,150
It was nobody's fault. They were
just cutting back. It was economics.

545
00:41:07,280 --> 00:41:10,477
- What are you gonna do?
- I don't know. I was, um...

546
00:41:11,080 --> 00:41:13,435
...thinkin' about fightin'.

547
00:41:14,840 --> 00:41:18,037
What about your eye? The doctor
said you shouldn't fight any more.

548
00:41:18,160 --> 00:41:22,836
No, no. He <i>recommended</i> I don't fight,
and I recommend that I do.

549
00:41:23,960 --> 00:41:27,191
- You'll go blind.
- Nobody's goin' blind. Honest, I see great.

550
00:41:27,320 --> 00:41:29,880
I see like a beagle or somethin' like that.

551
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:33,470
Oh, Rocky, you gave me your word
you wouldn't fight any more.

552
00:41:33,600 --> 00:41:36,194
I mean, if we need money,
<i>I</i> could get a job.

553
00:41:40,200 --> 00:41:42,555
You don't have to do that.

554
00:41:43,560 --> 00:41:48,634
Oh, sure. I... I can get my job back,
you know, part time, at the pet shop.

555
00:41:55,280 --> 00:41:58,033
But I'm the one
who's supposed to support.

556
00:41:59,160 --> 00:42:01,515
It's just for a little while.

557
00:42:04,400 --> 00:42:07,039
Listen, what if you catch
some pet-shop disease?

558
00:42:07,160 --> 00:42:11,312
There are no pet-shop diseases, Rocky.
I mean, I... really, I wanna work.

559
00:42:14,960 --> 00:42:17,554
Well, maybe you're right, you know.

560
00:42:18,240 --> 00:42:20,708
You know what's best, you know.

561
00:42:25,680 --> 00:42:28,433
Could you start dinner?
I'm startin' to get hungry.

562
00:42:28,560 --> 00:42:30,994
I just wanna finish my workout here, OK?

563
00:42:31,120 --> 00:42:33,076
Sure.

564
00:43:41,160 --> 00:43:43,515
Who the hell is that?!

565
00:43:45,240 --> 00:43:48,391
- Avon lady.
- Is that Rocky?

566
00:43:49,440 --> 00:43:52,910
Hey! I don't remember givin' you no key.

567
00:43:53,040 --> 00:43:56,237
Come on up here.
Well, the prodigal son returns!

568
00:43:56,360 --> 00:44:00,956
Don't look so bad, do ya? What's that?
A outer-space monster you brought?

569
00:44:01,080 --> 00:44:03,958
That's Butkus, my large dog.
What's that in your ear?

570
00:44:04,280 --> 00:44:08,114
What is it? Just a...
I hear stupid things better.

571
00:44:08,240 --> 00:44:11,198
Well, now, did you come here
to show me that dog?

572
00:44:11,320 --> 00:44:14,232
No. Mick, can I have my locker back?

573
00:44:14,360 --> 00:44:16,749
- What's on your mind?
- Fightin'.

574
00:44:17,160 --> 00:44:19,913
Fightin'? What? You wanna go blind?

575
00:44:20,200 --> 00:44:22,794
- Nobody's goin' blind.
- You heard what I said?

576
00:44:22,920 --> 00:44:25,275
Yeah, and the eye's great. No problem.

577
00:44:25,400 --> 00:44:28,312
Now, listen, every pug thinks
he has one good one left.

578
00:44:28,440 --> 00:44:32,069
Now forget it,
cos your fightin' career is over, kid.

579
00:44:32,200 --> 00:44:34,350
- Is that right?
- I think that's right.

580
00:44:34,480 --> 00:44:38,189
I spend my whole life gettin' a career.
I get one, and you tell me it's over.

581
00:44:38,560 --> 00:44:42,838
What's the matter? You shook the hell out
of the champion of the whole wide world.

582
00:44:42,960 --> 00:44:45,838
- You be happy with that.
- Maybe we can do better this time.

583
00:44:45,960 --> 00:44:48,997
- Or worse. What about that?
- Hey, yo, Mick.

584
00:44:49,120 --> 00:44:53,511
I done you a favour last time, you know.
Can you do me one this time?

585
00:44:54,840 --> 00:44:58,833
I don't know. You don't understand me.
I wanna show you somethin' now.

586
00:44:58,960 --> 00:45:03,351
Test you. Now, look, you look right there
at the end of my nose, will ya?

587
00:45:03,480 --> 00:45:05,550
- I wanna test you.
- Look at your nose.

588
00:45:05,680 --> 00:45:09,673
You look at my nose. When I bring my
finger in, you tell me when you see it.

589
00:45:10,040 --> 00:45:12,600
- There's the little thing. I see it.
- That's good.

590
00:45:12,720 --> 00:45:16,395
- I told you. It's OK.
- Now, wait. Now we'll try the other lamp.

591
00:45:16,520 --> 00:45:19,159
Now, look here, will ya? Now, tell me...

592
00:45:23,080 --> 00:45:25,196
- I see it.
- No, you see nothin'.

593
00:45:25,320 --> 00:45:29,711
Creed would have caved in the whole
side of your face. Now, forget it, kid.

594
00:45:29,840 --> 00:45:34,436
You got the heart, but you ain't got
the tooth no more. Now, forget it!

595
00:45:35,360 --> 00:45:37,396
- Is that right?
- That is right.

596
00:45:37,520 --> 00:45:42,196
Yeah? Well, maybe it's <i>you</i> who ain't
got it no more, you know that? Huh?

597
00:45:42,320 --> 00:45:44,993
Yeah. That's it.

598
00:45:47,200 --> 00:45:51,478
Now, look, you didn't even
see that comin', did ya? No.

599
00:45:51,840 --> 00:45:55,310
Well, that was from
a broken-down pug like me.

600
00:45:55,440 --> 00:45:58,398
What do you think
the champ would do to ya?

601
00:46:04,360 --> 00:46:08,512
- I don't know. Hurt me bad.
- No. He'd hurt you permanent.

602
00:46:08,640 --> 00:46:10,596
Permanent.

603
00:46:12,800 --> 00:46:14,756
You know, Mick, if...

604
00:46:17,200 --> 00:46:22,035
If I can't fight no more... maybe
I can help out around here, you know.

605
00:46:23,080 --> 00:46:25,719
Here? Well, sure, but...

606
00:46:26,440 --> 00:46:29,398
You know, you're like royalty here, kid.

607
00:46:29,520 --> 00:46:32,796
You want those guys to see you
carryin' towels and buckets around?

608
00:46:32,920 --> 00:46:35,275
Where's your dignity?

609
00:46:37,000 --> 00:46:40,470
I don't know how to say this,
you know. I just...

610
00:46:41,640 --> 00:46:43,596
I gotta be around it.

611
00:46:44,280 --> 00:46:46,236
I just g...

612
00:46:50,440 --> 00:46:54,194
All right, kid.
Will you come back tomorrow, huh?

613
00:46:59,200 --> 00:47:01,156
Thanks a lot, Mick.

614
00:47:23,080 --> 00:47:26,470
Look, as long as I'm gonna be
promoting this fight myself...

615
00:47:26,600 --> 00:47:28,556
...I want more pressure on for a rematch.

616
00:47:28,840 --> 00:47:32,469
Hey, we can get the same money
for the two top contenders.

617
00:47:32,600 --> 00:47:34,716
Why go after Balboa? Why?

618
00:47:34,840 --> 00:47:37,877
Because there's still
a lot of people that think he won.

619
00:47:38,000 --> 00:47:41,629
There's people accusin' me of havin'
the fight fixed, of bein' a fake...

620
00:47:41,760 --> 00:47:43,990
...and insultin' my kids at school.

621
00:47:44,200 --> 00:47:46,236
- You wanna hear the truth?
- Yeah.

622
00:47:46,360 --> 00:47:49,989
The truth is that last time
he was damn lucky.

623
00:47:50,120 --> 00:47:54,636
Now he's all finished. He's been hangin'
around doin' nothin' for six months.

624
00:47:54,760 --> 00:47:58,196
Any trainer worth anything
wouldn't have nothin' to do with him.

625
00:47:58,320 --> 00:48:01,357
Now, I say let's go after some new meat.

626
00:48:01,800 --> 00:48:03,756
Forget this bum.

627
00:48:04,600 --> 00:48:08,479
Do you think I beat him the last time?
Do you? Hm?

628
00:48:09,120 --> 00:48:12,999
- You got the decision.
- Man, I won, but I didn't beat him!

629
00:48:14,360 --> 00:48:16,920
What are you afraid of, Tony?

630
00:48:17,800 --> 00:48:19,631
- Honest?
- Yeah, honest.

631
00:48:27,440 --> 00:48:29,795
He's all wrong for us, baby.

632
00:48:30,560 --> 00:48:35,509
I saw you beat that man
like I never saw no man get beat before...

633
00:48:35,640 --> 00:48:38,757
...and the man kept coming after you.

634
00:48:40,960 --> 00:48:43,838
We don't need that kind of man in our life.

635
00:48:46,560 --> 00:48:48,516
I know what you're feelin'.

636
00:48:49,800 --> 00:48:51,756
Let it go.

637
00:48:53,480 --> 00:48:55,630
Let it go.

638
00:48:55,760 --> 00:48:57,716
You're the champ.

639
00:49:00,840 --> 00:49:06,790
Thank you. You're in charge of my public
relations. I want a new campaign started.

640
00:49:06,920 --> 00:49:11,869
I want somethin' done publicly to bring
this man out, to jar this man's pride...

641
00:49:12,000 --> 00:49:14,275
...to get the people around him talkin'.

642
00:49:14,400 --> 00:49:19,758
If we use this humiliation tactic,
you're setting yourself up as the bad guy.

643
00:49:19,880 --> 00:49:21,996
Whatever gets him in the ring.

644
00:49:46,520 --> 00:49:49,114
- What's happenin'?
- Hey.

645
00:49:49,240 --> 00:49:50,992
- What?
- Where's your heart?

646
00:49:51,120 --> 00:49:53,873
- What are you talkin' about?
- You heard me.

647
00:49:54,000 --> 00:49:55,672
Well, what's this?

648
00:50:04,720 --> 00:50:07,234
It's kinda funny, don't you think?

649
00:50:26,800 --> 00:50:29,075
<i>(Mickey)</i> Hey, Chico, listen. Hey, listen.

650
00:50:29,200 --> 00:50:32,112
What's with the grin?
How'd you get so happy with yourself?

651
00:50:32,240 --> 00:50:34,959
Let me tell you somethin'.
Snarl more, you see.

652
00:50:35,080 --> 00:50:39,232
Now, a good snarl can give you what
the Bible calls a psychological edge...

653
00:50:39,360 --> 00:50:43,148
...because you snarl on your punches...
Wait a minute. Hey, Rock!

654
00:50:43,560 --> 00:50:48,236
Rock, come here a minute. Show this
Latin lamebrain how to snarl and punch.

655
00:50:48,360 --> 00:50:50,316
Show him that.

656
00:50:52,120 --> 00:50:55,556
That's it, you see.
That's ugly! That's a snarl.

657
00:50:55,680 --> 00:50:59,150
Hey, John, will you empty them buckets?
They're flowin' over.

658
00:50:59,280 --> 00:51:00,918
- I'll do it.
- Let him do it.

659
00:51:01,040 --> 00:51:03,190
- I got it, Rock.
- Hey, Rock...

660
00:51:09,360 --> 00:51:11,316
Hey, wait a minute.

661
00:51:13,720 --> 00:51:15,233
Now you can take it.

662
00:51:15,360 --> 00:51:17,237
- Whoops.
- Hey!

663
00:51:17,920 --> 00:51:21,390
Can't you think of anything
tougher to say than "whoops"?

664
00:51:21,520 --> 00:51:23,875
Come on, hit that right. Bang!

665
00:51:28,480 --> 00:51:31,756
<i>(Mickey)</i> Wait a minute,
wait a minute. Hold it.

666
00:51:35,680 --> 00:51:37,989
All right. Come on, come on, come on.

667
00:51:45,000 --> 00:51:46,956
Yo, Rock.

668
00:51:48,040 --> 00:51:50,031
Yo, Tony. How you doin'?

669
00:51:50,160 --> 00:51:53,709
How am <i>I</i> doin'? How are <i>you</i> doin'?
I heard you was workin' in this dump.

670
00:51:53,840 --> 00:51:55,796
What are you doin'?

671
00:51:55,920 --> 00:51:58,753
I'm sweepin' up,
makin' a few bucks here and there.

672
00:51:58,880 --> 00:52:02,793
You ain't no janitor. You don't need
a job like this. Besides, you're Italian.

673
00:52:02,920 --> 00:52:06,117
- You come back and work for me.
- Well, what would I be doing?

674
00:52:06,240 --> 00:52:10,631
You mean, like, uh...
you know, like, collectin' or somethin'?

675
00:52:10,760 --> 00:52:13,991
What else? Come back, work on
the docks, you get some fresh air.

676
00:52:14,120 --> 00:52:18,989
- It stinks in here.
- I appreciate the offer, but, uh...

677
00:52:19,120 --> 00:52:22,908
...I can't do that stuff no more.
- It's healthy, huh?

678
00:52:23,040 --> 00:52:25,679
Now, look, I gotta go.
Take it easy, huh, champ?

679
00:52:25,800 --> 00:52:28,394
Yeah. See you around.

680
00:52:29,680 --> 00:52:32,035
Remember that guy, Rock?

681
00:52:52,440 --> 00:52:53,395
Yo!

682
00:52:54,320 --> 00:52:56,072
How's everybody
in the clubhouse tonight?

683
00:52:56,200 --> 00:52:59,476
- Oh, fine. How'd your day go?
- A million laughs. It was great.

684
00:52:59,600 --> 00:53:02,194
- You need some help with that?
- Yes.

685
00:53:03,120 --> 00:53:06,032
Hey, maybe you oughta stay home
and rest your stomach.

686
00:53:06,160 --> 00:53:11,075
- It's just part time. We need the money.
- Yeah, well, maybe you're right.

687
00:53:12,240 --> 00:53:14,629
There we go.

688
00:53:14,760 --> 00:53:18,958
That ain't my brand. I like oatmeal.
Listen, why don't we forget all this work?

689
00:53:19,080 --> 00:53:22,595
You wanna come home with me now?
Maybe I'll tell you a few jokes...

690
00:53:22,720 --> 00:53:25,029
...and maybe you'll laugh, you know. Huh?

691
00:53:25,160 --> 00:53:28,232
We need a few laughs in our life.
What do you think? Maybe?

692
00:53:28,360 --> 00:53:29,315
- Yes.
- Maybe?

693
00:53:29,440 --> 00:53:32,273
- Maybe.
- Maybe? OK. Let's get outta here, OK?

694
00:53:32,400 --> 00:53:34,470
- OK.
- Here we go.

695
00:53:34,600 --> 00:53:39,469
Hey, listen, Adrian. Listen to this one.
Why do cows wear bells?

696
00:53:39,600 --> 00:53:42,478
- Why?
- Cos their horns don't work.

697
00:53:42,600 --> 00:53:45,353
Is that killin' ya? No? Huh?

698
00:53:46,480 --> 00:53:50,758
They really used to like it in third grade.
I used to break everyone up with that one.

699
00:53:54,360 --> 00:53:56,237
<i>(man)</i> Yo!

700
00:53:56,680 --> 00:53:59,478
- You really sweep good, man!
<i>- (laughter)</i>

701
00:54:00,160 --> 00:54:02,116
Is he talking to you?

702
00:54:02,240 --> 00:54:06,950
Nah, he probably has me mixed up
with somebody else. Come on.

703
00:54:08,320 --> 00:54:10,231
Italian chicken.

704
00:54:11,360 --> 00:54:14,352
Boy, you guys got the easy life.

705
00:54:14,480 --> 00:54:18,393
Hey, how you guys doin'?
Did anybody move today, you know, huh?

706
00:54:18,520 --> 00:54:22,433
How's life in the bowl?
You gotta exercise once in a while.

707
00:54:22,560 --> 00:54:25,358
Would you like a little snack
or somethin'? Here you go.

708
00:54:25,480 --> 00:54:29,359
Come on, Cuff. Hey, Link, what,
are you drowning down there? Huh?

709
00:54:29,480 --> 00:54:33,029
Hey, wanna hear some TV?
Huh? Wanna hear some TV?

710
00:54:36,000 --> 00:54:39,595
<i>... the Los Angeles Rams. The Rams</i>
<i>defeated the Buccaneers in overtime...</i>

711
00:54:39,720 --> 00:54:42,154
<i>... 13 to 10 on Frank Corell's 45-yard...</i>

712
00:54:42,280 --> 00:54:45,636
Hey, Butkus.
Come here, Butkus. Come on, boy.

713
00:54:46,520 --> 00:54:49,159
What'd you do today, huh?

714
00:54:49,280 --> 00:54:51,077
Did you bark at anybody today?

715
00:54:51,200 --> 00:54:56,149
Adrian! Sometimes I look at Butkus
and I don't think he's a normal canine.

716
00:54:56,280 --> 00:54:58,396
- What do you think he is?
- I don't know.

717
00:54:58,520 --> 00:55:02,513
He just don't look like a regular dog to me
sometimes when I look inside there.

718
00:55:02,640 --> 00:55:06,349
<i>(TV) Earlier today I was down</i>
<i>at Apollo Creed's palatial gym...</i>

719
00:55:06,480 --> 00:55:11,235
<i>... and, as usual, the champion was not</i>
<i>at a loss for words about Rocky Balboa.</i>

720
00:55:11,360 --> 00:55:13,794
<i>I know a lot of people</i>
<i>wanna see me in a rematch...</i>

721
00:55:13,920 --> 00:55:16,753
<i>... with a timid fellow</i>
<i>called the Italian Stallion.</i>

722
00:55:16,880 --> 00:55:21,271
<i>But this man does not have the honour</i>
<i>to meet me in the ring. Or is it Scallion?</i>

723
00:55:21,400 --> 00:55:23,960
<i>- What is your name?</i>
<i>- Balboa did officially retire.</i>

724
00:55:24,080 --> 00:55:26,548
<i>The bum's hidin'.</i>
<i>He doesn't wanna face me.</i>

725
00:55:26,680 --> 00:55:29,911
<i>- He's scared.</i>
<i>- There's more here than meets the eye.</i>

726
00:55:30,040 --> 00:55:33,316
<i>You've been under scrutiny</i>
<i>since that split-decision victory.</i>

727
00:55:33,440 --> 00:55:36,796
<i>A lot of reporters, Apollo, including me,</i>
<i>thought it was an even draw.</i>

728
00:55:36,920 --> 00:55:40,310
<i>(Apollo) That's your opinion,</i>
<i>but now I'm ready to have a rematch...</i>

729
00:55:40,440 --> 00:55:44,877
<i>... to prove that this lucky club fighter</i>
<i>does not have the skill...</i>

730
00:55:45,000 --> 00:55:48,037
<i>... to last five minutes in the ring</i>
<i>with a superior athlete.</i>

731
00:55:48,160 --> 00:55:50,993
<i>The man's runnin', he's hidin'.</i>
<i>He doesn't wanna face me.</i>

732
00:55:51,120 --> 00:55:55,272
<i>So I say to you, Rocky Balboa, that</i>
<i>I want the American people to know...</i>

733
00:55:55,400 --> 00:55:58,631
<i>... I want the world to know that</i>
<i>I'm ready to meet you anywhere.</i>

734
00:55:58,760 --> 00:56:02,435
<i>Any place, any time, I will meet</i>
<i>and defeat this so-called fighter...</i>

735
00:56:02,560 --> 00:56:06,951
<i>... the Italian Stallion, if the man only has</i>
<i>the guts to give me a call. Call me collect.</i>

736
00:56:07,080 --> 00:56:08,991
<i>Call me, Balboa!</i>

737
00:56:09,120 --> 00:56:12,510
<i>This would be a legitimate rematch,</i>
<i>the boxer against the puncher.</i>

738
00:56:12,640 --> 00:56:15,200
<i>Everyone wants to see them</i>
<i>back in the ring.</i>

739
00:56:15,320 --> 00:56:18,676
<i>But there's only one problem:</i>
<i>Where is Rocky Balboa?</i>

740
00:56:20,000 --> 00:56:21,353
Ugly bum!

741
00:56:29,440 --> 00:56:31,829
You know, I was thinking that, uh...

742
00:56:32,760 --> 00:56:35,399
...I ain't supposed to
do no commercials and...

743
00:56:35,520 --> 00:56:38,478
...I ain't supposed to
work in no meat house.

744
00:56:38,600 --> 00:56:41,114
I'm supposed to be a fighter.

745
00:56:41,240 --> 00:56:43,595
But you... you gave that up.

746
00:56:44,320 --> 00:56:46,072
Mm.

747
00:56:46,200 --> 00:56:49,351
I think I'm becomin' a nobody again, too.

748
00:56:49,480 --> 00:56:52,392
- In whose eyes? Not mine.
- In mine.

749
00:56:53,560 --> 00:56:56,028
In here.

750
00:56:57,640 --> 00:56:59,995
- We'll get by.
- That's just it.

751
00:57:01,200 --> 00:57:04,431
I don't want just to get by
the hard way, you know?

752
00:57:04,560 --> 00:57:08,553
I want you to have good things.
I want the kid to have good things.

753
00:57:08,680 --> 00:57:11,240
We'll have 'em.

754
00:57:11,360 --> 00:57:14,557
I just think we need 'em now, don't you?

755
00:57:15,320 --> 00:57:17,276
Rocky, please...

756
00:57:17,720 --> 00:57:20,154
You don't have to prove anything.

757
00:57:21,640 --> 00:57:23,756
Adrian, it's all I know.

758
00:57:25,080 --> 00:57:27,514
I don't want you to do it.

759
00:57:28,640 --> 00:57:30,596
It's all I know.

760
00:57:33,640 --> 00:57:35,596
Adrian?

761
00:57:37,200 --> 00:57:39,156
You know...

762
00:57:40,880 --> 00:57:44,793
...I never asked you to stop
bein' a woman, you know?

763
00:57:44,920 --> 00:57:49,789
Please, I'm askin' you, please...
don't ask me to stop bein' a man.

764
00:57:50,880 --> 00:57:52,836
Please.

765
00:57:55,120 --> 00:57:57,076
<i>(knocking)</i>

766
00:57:59,920 --> 00:58:01,876
<i>(knocking)</i>

767
00:58:04,000 --> 00:58:05,956
<i>(knocking)</i>

768
00:58:09,040 --> 00:58:10,996
<i>(knocking)</i>

769
00:58:21,360 --> 00:58:24,352
I think we oughta knock his block off.

770
00:58:24,480 --> 00:58:26,789
- Absolutely.
- <i>(Adrian)</i> Rocky...

771
00:58:30,000 --> 00:58:31,956
I'm sorry.

772
00:58:39,240 --> 00:58:41,196
Let's do it.

773
00:58:42,920 --> 00:58:46,230
Apollo! Apollo! Has a site
been chosen for the rematch?

774
00:58:46,360 --> 00:58:48,635
It will be in the Philadelphia Spectrum...

775
00:58:48,760 --> 00:58:51,035
...cos I want this man's
home town to see this.

776
00:58:51,160 --> 00:58:54,709
I want all of Philadelphia,
all of America, the whole world...

777
00:58:54,840 --> 00:58:57,559
...to see me destroy this man
after two short rounds.

778
00:58:57,680 --> 00:59:02,959
After this fight he's gonna have to donate
what's left of his body to science.

779
00:59:03,080 --> 00:59:07,198
Rocky, what do you think about
the fight taking place in the Spectrum?

780
00:59:07,320 --> 00:59:09,959
- Well, I'm very happy about that.
- Why?

781
00:59:10,080 --> 00:59:12,958
Well, it's only about
ten minutes from my house.

782
00:59:13,360 --> 00:59:17,319
Apollo, people say that you lost the first
fight, a victim of the southpaw jinx.

783
00:59:17,440 --> 00:59:20,750
- Did fighting a left-hander throw you off?
- Southpaw jinx nothin'!

784
00:59:20,880 --> 00:59:23,952
I took the fight too lightly
and this man was just plain lucky.

785
00:59:24,080 --> 00:59:27,436
But this time - this time -
you all will see the real Apollo Creed.

786
00:59:27,560 --> 00:59:29,755
The world's gonna see
the real Apollo Creed.

787
00:59:29,880 --> 00:59:34,715
Lightnin' fast and hard to catch.
No playin', no jivin' - just business.

788
00:59:35,440 --> 00:59:39,831
Rocky, do you think you have
a chance this time against Apollo?

789
00:59:39,960 --> 00:59:43,509
- I don't know. He looks pretty mad.
<i>- (laughter)</i>

790
00:59:43,640 --> 00:59:48,395
- Me and Mick, we're gonna try our best.
- His lungs he's gonna punch out.

791
00:59:48,520 --> 00:59:51,876
- Now, who's that? Al Capone?
- I would sweat you.

792
00:59:52,840 --> 00:59:56,116
Look here, a lot of people
may not like me, and that's OK.

793
00:59:56,240 --> 01:00:00,153
But come November, Apollo Creed will
provide the ultimate gala spectacle...

794
01:00:00,280 --> 01:00:03,272
...on Thanksgiving,
in front of this man's home crowd.

795
01:00:03,400 --> 01:00:05,470
I'm gonna drop him like a bad habit.

796
01:00:05,600 --> 01:00:09,912
Rocky, your pay is substantial.
What are you gonna do with the money?

797
01:00:10,040 --> 01:00:13,953
The first thing I gotta do
is I gotta pay the rent, you know.

798
01:00:14,080 --> 01:00:18,039
And then I made this list on the way over.
I was just thinkin' of things to do.

799
01:00:18,160 --> 01:00:21,994
I'd like to get a couple of hats
and a motorcycle and...

800
01:00:22,120 --> 01:00:25,715
...a couple of quarts of perfume
for Adrian - she likes to smell good.

801
01:00:25,840 --> 01:00:29,549
Some Muppet toys - you know,
Ernie and Big Bird and that frog.

802
01:00:29,680 --> 01:00:33,389
- What's his name? Kermit or somethin'?
- I don't know.

803
01:00:34,640 --> 01:00:38,792
I thought maybe a statue for the church,
and a snow-cone machine for you, Paulie.

804
01:00:38,920 --> 01:00:41,593
- You like snow cones, don't you?
- Yeah.

805
01:00:41,720 --> 01:00:45,030
Rocky, got anything derogatory
to say about the champ?

806
01:00:45,160 --> 01:00:47,720
Derogatory... Yeah. He's great.

807
01:00:48,040 --> 01:00:50,998
How about some clowning shots, Apollo?

808
01:00:51,120 --> 01:00:53,918
Does this look like a circus to you, man?

809
01:00:55,240 --> 01:00:57,196
Come November, you're mine.

810
01:01:00,120 --> 01:01:02,475
- He's very upset.
- Ah, well.

811
01:01:06,520 --> 01:01:09,034
<i>(Mickey)</i> See how smooth
he moves there?

812
01:01:09,160 --> 01:01:11,913
- See how he pumps that jab in your eye?
- Yeah.

813
01:01:12,960 --> 01:01:15,838
You got guts to go back
in the ring with him, kid.

814
01:01:15,960 --> 01:01:18,030
Thanks a lot, Mick.

815
01:01:18,160 --> 01:01:21,277
You see, your style's
too easy to figure out.

816
01:01:22,360 --> 01:01:26,399
Left-handed fighters, they're the worst.
They lead with their face mostly.

817
01:01:26,520 --> 01:01:29,876
Tryin' to throw that big left.
Right's no damn good.

818
01:01:30,680 --> 01:01:33,035
They oughta outlaw southpaws.

819
01:01:33,160 --> 01:01:35,310
Why didn't you tell me this before?

820
01:01:35,440 --> 01:01:38,398
I didn't wanna hurt your feelings.
Now, look...

821
01:01:39,200 --> 01:01:43,239
...to pull this miracle off,
you gotta change everything.

822
01:01:43,360 --> 01:01:46,955
You gotta learn to be a right-handed
fighter. This'll confuse Apollo...

823
01:01:47,080 --> 01:01:49,355
...and it'll protect that bad eye.

824
01:01:50,520 --> 01:01:54,069
- I can't learn how to fight right-handed.
- What's can't?

825
01:01:54,200 --> 01:01:57,033
There ain't no can'ts! There's no can'ts.

826
01:01:57,160 --> 01:02:00,516
Now, he will beat you
uglier than you are now.

827
01:02:00,640 --> 01:02:04,792
Now, listen, you start fightin' right-handed
and then you change suddenly...

828
01:02:04,920 --> 01:02:08,230
...and that'll make history,
but first you gotta get speed.

829
01:02:08,360 --> 01:02:10,954
Demon speed. Speed's what we need.

830
01:02:11,080 --> 01:02:14,231
We need greasy, fast speed!

831
01:02:14,520 --> 01:02:17,751
Now, I'll show ya a trick
how to get some speed in them legs.

832
01:02:17,880 --> 01:02:21,236
- Do you have to wear that sweatshirt?
- It brings me luck, you know?

833
01:02:21,360 --> 01:02:24,989
You know what it brings? It brings flies.
I want you to try - listen to me.

834
01:02:25,120 --> 01:02:27,714
I want you to try to
chase this little chicken.

835
01:02:28,120 --> 01:02:30,839
What do I gotta chase that for?
It's embarrassing.

836
01:02:30,960 --> 01:02:32,757
First, because I said so.

837
01:02:32,880 --> 01:02:37,317
Second, because chicken-chasin' is how
we always used to train in the old days.

838
01:02:37,440 --> 01:02:40,716
You catch this thing,
you can catch greased lightning. Ready?

839
01:02:40,840 --> 01:02:43,912
Well, I'd rather eat it than chase it.
It ain't very mature.

840
01:02:44,040 --> 01:02:46,998
Neither are you very mature!
Listen, get this thing.

841
01:02:47,120 --> 01:02:50,476
- I'm a fighter. I ain't a farmer.
- Come on at it! Go on and get him!

842
01:02:50,600 --> 01:02:54,309
Get him! Get him! Get him! Come on!
What's the matter with ya? Get him!

843
01:02:55,200 --> 01:02:57,350
Pick him up! Pick him up!

844
01:02:57,840 --> 01:02:59,558
Pull him round!

845
01:03:00,800 --> 01:03:04,998
What's the matter? Are you standin' still
or somethin'? Speed! Speed!

846
01:03:05,120 --> 01:03:07,554
Can't you catch a little chicken? Huh?

847
01:03:07,680 --> 01:03:10,797
Come on! Move your tail! Move your tail!

848
01:03:11,120 --> 01:03:14,078
You look like a girl out there.
What's the matter with ya?

849
01:03:14,200 --> 01:03:16,430
I feel like a Kentucky fried idiot.

850
01:03:17,720 --> 01:03:21,759
Wake up, will ya? Will ya wake up?
Come on! Come on. Give it. Give it!

851
01:03:21,880 --> 01:03:24,394
Yo, Rock.
What's the matter with my sister?

852
01:03:24,600 --> 01:03:28,878
Well, I wish you'd go talk to her. Adrian
don't like this none. She's started cryin'.

853
01:03:29,000 --> 01:03:32,310
- She don't like me fightin'.
- What's with this domestic stuff?

854
01:03:32,440 --> 01:03:35,910
Tend to the business, will ya?!
Jab that till it hurts!

855
01:03:36,040 --> 01:03:39,669
500 times without stopping.
Do you hear me? 500 times.

856
01:03:39,800 --> 01:03:42,872
- I wanna use my other arm.
- If you do, I'm gonna chop it off.

857
01:03:43,000 --> 01:03:45,230
- Is that clear?
- I'll figure somethin'.

858
01:03:45,360 --> 01:03:47,920
I wish you would, Paulie. I appreciate it.

859
01:03:48,240 --> 01:03:51,277
I'm sorry. Are you finished?
Can we go to work?

860
01:03:51,400 --> 01:03:56,110
That would be nice. Now, hit that bag.
Hit it. Jab it till it hurts. Go ahead!

861
01:03:56,520 --> 01:03:59,910
- Three... four...
- I want 500 high ones.

862
01:04:00,040 --> 01:04:02,998
- Go!
- What was that? Seven or eight?

863
01:04:05,960 --> 01:04:09,953
One, two. One, two.
One, two. Come on. Turn it over.

864
01:04:10,080 --> 01:04:14,596
Snap it. Snap it. Come on.
Dig it! Dig it! Dig it!

865
01:04:15,480 --> 01:04:17,311
All right, pick it up.

866
01:04:17,440 --> 01:04:19,556
Come on. Pick 'em up. Pick 'em up.

867
01:04:19,680 --> 01:04:22,513
Faster! Faster! Faster!

868
01:04:22,640 --> 01:04:24,596
Come on! Faster!

869
01:04:32,040 --> 01:04:33,314
Time!

870
01:04:38,960 --> 01:04:40,916
Time!

871
01:04:45,000 --> 01:04:48,151
Get up! Get me another one, all right?

872
01:04:48,280 --> 01:04:51,955
- Ease up on these sparrin' partners.
- You just get me another, man.

873
01:04:59,400 --> 01:05:03,439
Time! What's the matter?
That bag too fast for ya?

874
01:05:03,560 --> 01:05:07,314
<i>(crowd chants) Apollo! Apollo! Apollo!</i>

875
01:05:13,320 --> 01:05:15,629
You're gonna pound
that sass right out of him.

876
01:05:15,760 --> 01:05:20,038
Last time we shoulda won,
but this time you're gonna be scary, kid.

877
01:05:20,160 --> 01:05:23,994
You're gonna be a greasy,
fast, Italian monster!

878
01:05:24,120 --> 01:05:27,635
You're gonna eat lightning!
You're gonna crap thunder!

879
01:05:27,760 --> 01:05:30,069
We'll have to put you in a cage, kid.

880
01:05:32,560 --> 01:05:35,677
- Let's take a break, all right?
- Break? What break?

881
01:05:35,800 --> 01:05:40,237
Where are you goin'? We're not finished.
Hey, I said where the hell you goin'?

882
01:06:03,600 --> 01:06:05,556
Ooh!

883
01:06:06,440 --> 01:06:08,396
Ohh...

884
01:06:09,440 --> 01:06:11,874
<i>(Mickey)</i> Speed! Speed!

885
01:06:12,000 --> 01:06:14,150
Catch that punk!

886
01:06:14,280 --> 01:06:18,512
Speed! Speed!
Can't you catch that little squirt?

887
01:06:18,640 --> 01:06:22,076
Can't you? Get the lead out!

888
01:06:22,200 --> 01:06:23,997
Move! Move! Fast!

889
01:06:24,120 --> 01:06:27,396
You look dead. If you're gonna
catch that little speedball...

890
01:06:27,520 --> 01:06:29,556
...you're gonna catch Creed easy.

891
01:06:29,760 --> 01:06:31,637
Come on! Move! Move!

892
01:06:31,760 --> 01:06:33,478
Right. Time!

893
01:06:33,600 --> 01:06:35,955
Hey, dead ass. Get over here.

894
01:06:38,200 --> 01:06:40,555
Hey, are you sick, kid?

895
01:06:41,280 --> 01:06:43,953
Kid, what's the matter with you?

896
01:06:44,080 --> 01:06:47,516
- Nothin'.
- Let me tell you somethin', kid.

897
01:06:47,640 --> 01:06:53,988
Now, for a 45-minute fight,
you gotta train hard for 45,000 minutes.

898
01:06:54,120 --> 01:06:59,148
45,000. That's ten weeks.
That's ten hours a day. You listenin'?

899
01:06:59,600 --> 01:07:01,750
And you ain't even trained one.

900
01:07:02,000 --> 01:07:05,629
I don't know what the hell you're
waitin' for. What are you waitin' for?

901
01:07:05,760 --> 01:07:07,830
I don't know.

902
01:07:07,960 --> 01:07:09,916
Suit yourself.

903
01:07:11,160 --> 01:07:14,994
- Yo, Rocky.
- Hey, yo, Paulie. How you doin'?

904
01:07:15,120 --> 01:07:19,716
I'm worried about you. I've been watchin'.
Your head ain't screwed on right.

905
01:07:19,840 --> 01:07:22,877
Nah, come on. I'm doin' OK.
You know, I've been thinking.

906
01:07:23,000 --> 01:07:26,834
Would you like to work in my corner?
Wanna get involved in this fight?

907
01:07:27,200 --> 01:07:31,034
- What? Watchin' you get murdered?
- Oh, come on. I'm doin' OK.

908
01:07:31,160 --> 01:07:34,470
My sister got you so guilty,
you're runnin' all over the place.

909
01:07:34,600 --> 01:07:36,909
- She'll be all right.
- It ain't all right.

910
01:07:37,040 --> 01:07:39,349
Hey, Paulie, it's OK, all right?

911
01:07:39,480 --> 01:07:42,950
- It's not OK.
- Just leave Adrian alone, all right?

912
01:07:53,400 --> 01:07:55,595
Yo, Adrian! Where are ya?

913
01:07:55,720 --> 01:07:59,235
- Paulie.
- Yeah, Paulie. What the hell you doin'?

914
01:07:59,360 --> 01:08:01,669
- What do you mean?
- What the hell you doin'?

915
01:08:01,800 --> 01:08:05,554
- About what?
- About messin' up that guy over there.

916
01:08:06,800 --> 01:08:09,075
Don't start. I'm just
trying to keep him safe.

917
01:08:09,200 --> 01:08:11,919
Yeah, what?
Feedin' these goddamn squirrels?

918
01:08:12,040 --> 01:08:15,350
Did I teach you how to do that?
Ditchin' a guy when he needs your help?

919
01:08:15,480 --> 01:08:19,553
- I can't believe my ears.
- You didn't teach me anything, Paulie.

920
01:08:19,680 --> 01:08:22,672
- And I never hurt Rocky.
- You're messin' up his brain real bad.

921
01:08:22,800 --> 01:08:25,678
- That's not what I'm doing.
- Yeah, don't tell me!

922
01:08:25,800 --> 01:08:28,792
- He's gonna get hurt because of you!
- It's not true.

923
01:08:28,920 --> 01:08:30,717
- Don't say that!
- I'm sayin' it.

924
01:08:31,160 --> 01:08:35,073
- Come across and tell him it's all right.
- If he goes blind, you walk away.

925
01:08:35,200 --> 01:08:37,555
I can't. I love him. You don't!

926
01:08:42,960 --> 01:08:45,520
What are you doin'?

927
01:08:45,640 --> 01:08:47,710
What are you doin'? What's wrong?

928
01:08:47,840 --> 01:08:49,831
Adrian, what's the matter?

929
01:08:53,280 --> 01:08:55,350
Come on. Where are your guts?

930
01:08:55,480 --> 01:08:57,436
What's your problem, Mick?

931
01:08:57,560 --> 01:08:59,357
- <i>My</i> problem?
- Yeah.

932
01:08:59,480 --> 01:09:03,029
You got the problem, kid.
You got a ticker problem.

933
01:09:03,160 --> 01:09:05,720
What's the matter?
You got nothin' left inside?

934
01:09:05,840 --> 01:09:09,310
Cos you're trainin' like a damn bum,
you know that?

935
01:09:09,440 --> 01:09:11,396
- Bum?
- A bum.

936
01:09:13,000 --> 01:09:15,639
Maybe you're right.
Maybe I ain't got it no more.

937
01:09:15,760 --> 01:09:20,276
All right. Then don't you waste
my time no more. You hear that?

938
01:09:20,400 --> 01:09:23,233
Go away!
Go back to the docks where you belong.

939
01:09:23,360 --> 01:09:26,716
You go back to bein' a two-bit nothin'!

940
01:09:26,840 --> 01:09:31,755
But don't you ever come back here again,
because I'm too old to waste my time...

941
01:09:31,880 --> 01:09:35,031
...tryin' to train
a no-good loser like you, you bum!

942
01:09:35,160 --> 01:09:37,469
- They want you across the street.
- What's up?

943
01:09:37,600 --> 01:09:39,556
Your wife's sick.

944
01:09:48,480 --> 01:09:53,838
Mr Balboa? I'm Dr Cooper. The baby is
fine, even though it's a month premature.

945
01:09:53,960 --> 01:09:55,757
- What is it?
- It's a boy.

946
01:09:55,880 --> 01:09:58,075
Holy smoke. I didn't know she could do it.

947
01:09:58,200 --> 01:10:00,316
How's Adrian? Where <i>is</i> Adrian?

948
01:10:00,440 --> 01:10:02,795
She's had complications.

949
01:10:04,400 --> 01:10:05,628
Like what?

950
01:10:05,760 --> 01:10:08,069
She was haemorrhaging
when she was brought in.

951
01:10:08,200 --> 01:10:12,478
The premature delivery was most likely
caused by strain of overwork...

952
01:10:12,600 --> 01:10:16,718
...and the sudden loss of blood
has caused her to slip into a coma.

953
01:10:45,120 --> 01:10:47,076
Adrian, it's... it's me.

954
01:10:54,120 --> 01:10:56,714
They said outside you're very sick, but I...

955
01:10:57,960 --> 01:10:59,916
I don't wanna believe that.

956
01:11:02,480 --> 01:11:04,835
Maybe you're just tired, you know.

957
01:11:08,280 --> 01:11:13,513
Don't worry about nothin'.
You just sleep as long as you want, OK?

958
01:11:13,640 --> 01:11:16,473
And I'm gonna be here
when you wake up.

959
01:11:16,600 --> 01:11:18,556
<i>(knocking)</i>

960
01:11:24,920 --> 01:11:28,469
Rocky, come on.
You're not doin' any good here.

961
01:11:28,600 --> 01:11:30,636
Let's go see the kid.

962
01:11:30,760 --> 01:11:33,115
No. We gotta see him together.

963
01:11:34,280 --> 01:11:36,840
It's OK. We gotta see him together.

964
01:11:50,920 --> 01:11:54,469
Mr Balboa, visiting hours are over.

965
01:11:55,520 --> 01:11:57,875
Can't I stay? I'll be quiet.

966
01:11:59,240 --> 01:12:02,073
I'm sorry. Hospital rules.

967
01:12:04,320 --> 01:12:06,834
I can't do any more of this watchin' stuff.

968
01:12:13,240 --> 01:12:15,196
Do you have a chapel?

969
01:12:16,120 --> 01:12:18,076
Yes, we do.

970
01:12:25,920 --> 01:12:27,876
Good night.

971
01:12:49,800 --> 01:12:51,756
Hi, Rock.

972
01:12:52,320 --> 01:12:53,230
Uh...

973
01:12:55,880 --> 01:12:59,759
That Adrian... she's a good girl.

974
01:13:01,880 --> 01:13:04,838
Me, you know, I'm sorry for both of ya.

975
01:13:05,600 --> 01:13:07,556
Hm?

976
01:13:08,080 --> 01:13:11,117
Well... there's nothin' I can do, is there?

977
01:13:11,880 --> 01:13:13,836
Except...

978
01:13:16,200 --> 01:13:20,990
I'd like to tell you somethin' once,
and then I ain't gonna say it again.

979
01:13:21,400 --> 01:13:24,676
Well, Rocky, you got a... another shot.

980
01:13:24,800 --> 01:13:26,756
It's a second shot.

981
01:13:27,360 --> 01:13:31,638
At the, uh... I don't know,
the biggest title in the world.

982
01:13:33,680 --> 01:13:36,513
And you're gonna be swappin' punches...

983
01:13:36,640 --> 01:13:40,599
...with the most dangerous
fighter in the world.

984
01:13:42,280 --> 01:13:47,195
And just in case, you know,
your brain ain't workin' so good...

985
01:13:48,320 --> 01:13:50,754
...all this happens pretty soon.

986
01:13:51,560 --> 01:13:53,551
And you ain't ready.

987
01:13:54,840 --> 01:13:57,195
You're nowhere near in shape.

988
01:13:57,880 --> 01:14:01,668
So I say, you know, for God's sake...

989
01:14:01,960 --> 01:14:06,351
...why don't you stand up and fight
this guy hard, like you done before?

990
01:14:06,480 --> 01:14:08,835
That was beautiful!

991
01:14:10,720 --> 01:14:13,678
But don't lay down
in front of him like this!

992
01:14:13,800 --> 01:14:17,588
Like a... I don't know,
like some kind of mongrel or somethin'.

993
01:14:17,720 --> 01:14:21,156
Cos he's gonna kick your face in pieces.

994
01:14:21,280 --> 01:14:25,831
You know that? That's right.
This guy just don't wanna win, you know.

995
01:14:25,960 --> 01:14:28,918
He wants to bury ya.
He wants to humiliate ya.

996
01:14:29,040 --> 01:14:30,951
He wants to prove to the whole world...

997
01:14:31,080 --> 01:14:35,471
...that it was nothin' but
some kind of a freak the first time out.

998
01:14:35,600 --> 01:14:38,558
He said you're a one-time lucky bum.

999
01:14:41,880 --> 01:14:43,996
Well, now...

1000
01:14:44,120 --> 01:14:46,190
I don't...

1001
01:14:46,320 --> 01:14:48,515
I don't wanna get mad...

1002
01:14:48,640 --> 01:14:51,677
...in a biblical place like this...

1003
01:14:51,800 --> 01:14:56,396
...but I think you're a hell of a lot
more than that, kid. A hell of a lot.

1004
01:15:02,400 --> 01:15:07,793
But, no, wait a minute. If you wanna
blow it, if you wanna blow this thing...

1005
01:15:07,920 --> 01:15:10,480
...dammit, I'm gonna blow it with ya.

1006
01:15:12,160 --> 01:15:15,118
Do you wanna stay here?
I'll stay with you.

1007
01:15:16,000 --> 01:15:17,956
I'll stay with you.

1008
01:15:19,080 --> 01:15:21,036
Yeah.

1009
01:15:23,200 --> 01:15:25,760
I'll stay and pray.

1010
01:15:25,880 --> 01:15:28,235
What have I got to lose?

1011
01:15:49,360 --> 01:15:51,715
It's gonna be OK.

1012
01:16:19,480 --> 01:16:24,429
"'There ain't no other trail to the ranch,
or no shorter one."'

1013
01:16:24,560 --> 01:16:27,518
"'Oh, yes, there is' said Marvel."

1014
01:16:27,640 --> 01:16:33,351
"'When I was a kid, I helped my old man
trail some cattle up from the border."'

1015
01:16:33,720 --> 01:16:36,359
Can you hear me, Adrian?

1016
01:16:36,480 --> 01:16:38,914
Keep listening. Keep listening.

1017
01:16:40,560 --> 01:16:45,156
"After breakfast, Bruce watched
the party get away on the chase."

1018
01:16:45,280 --> 01:16:49,273
"He saw Cora and Kay and Bud...

1019
01:16:49,400 --> 01:16:53,393
...start up the valley
15 minutes ahead of the others."

1020
01:16:53,520 --> 01:16:55,476
"At the last minute, the girl..."

1021
01:17:08,480 --> 01:17:11,199
Well, I just wrote
this thing for you, Adrian.

1022
01:17:11,320 --> 01:17:13,629
I don't know... maybe you'll like it.

1023
01:17:13,760 --> 01:17:16,274
I'll just read it to ya, cos, uh...

1024
01:17:16,400 --> 01:17:19,676
"Remember when we was on ice skates

1025
01:17:19,800 --> 01:17:23,031
And I thought you were
supposed to be great?"

1026
01:17:23,160 --> 01:17:26,755
"But I kept givin' you lip
And you kept tryin' to slip

1027
01:17:26,880 --> 01:17:29,314
So I could catch you?"

1028
01:17:29,440 --> 01:17:33,877
"That was our first date
And after that every day was great."

1029
01:17:34,800 --> 01:17:37,189
"So now I want you to know

1030
01:17:37,320 --> 01:17:39,470
That wherever you go

1031
01:17:39,600 --> 01:17:42,114
Atlantic City or in the snow

1032
01:17:43,080 --> 01:17:45,275
Don't worry about a thing

1033
01:17:45,400 --> 01:17:48,073
Cos as long as I got this ring

1034
01:17:48,200 --> 01:17:50,873
I'll always be there to catch you."

1035
01:18:59,960 --> 01:19:01,916
I knew you'd come back.

1036
01:19:11,120 --> 01:19:13,076
<i>(Rocky)</i> Thank God.

1037
01:19:17,320 --> 01:19:21,199
Anybody want a refill?
Adrian, it cost six bucks a bottle.

1038
01:19:21,320 --> 01:19:25,029
- I don't need that. I ain't drinkin' now.
- So, you haven't seen the baby?

1039
01:19:25,160 --> 01:19:27,674
- I was waitin' to see him together.
- I seen the kid.

1040
01:19:28,080 --> 01:19:31,152
The kid's a winner.
He's got forearms like you, Mickey.

1041
01:19:31,280 --> 01:19:34,477
<i>- (nurse clears throat)</i>
- Here he is now. Look.

1042
01:19:37,480 --> 01:19:39,789
- There's your mommy.
- Oh, baby!

1043
01:19:42,760 --> 01:19:44,796
Is that it?

1044
01:19:47,640 --> 01:19:50,438
- I can't believe it. He's ours?
- Yeah.

1045
01:19:50,560 --> 01:19:52,357
- He's really ours?
- Thank you.

1046
01:19:52,480 --> 01:19:56,519
Come on. You done all the work.
Adrian, I can't believe you done this.

1047
01:19:56,640 --> 01:20:00,030
- Believe me, we did.
- Oh, no. He ain't got a name.

1048
01:20:00,160 --> 01:20:03,072
- What do you wanna call him?
- Paulie's a great name.

1049
01:20:04,560 --> 01:20:06,915
Yeah, Paulie's a pretty good name.

1050
01:20:07,240 --> 01:20:10,835
- What about after the father?
- Rocky Junior?

1051
01:20:10,960 --> 01:20:13,155
- Come on. You really wanna do that?
- Yes.

1052
01:20:13,280 --> 01:20:17,068
Adrian, he's the best I ever seen.
You really done good.

1053
01:20:18,760 --> 01:20:22,150
You look so tired.
Why don't you go get some sleep?

1054
01:20:22,280 --> 01:20:25,829
Oh, no, no. I feel great.
Listen, I been thinkin'...

1055
01:20:25,960 --> 01:20:29,236
...if you don't want me
mixin' with Creed no more...

1056
01:20:29,360 --> 01:20:31,510
...we'll make out some other
kind of way, you know.

1057
01:20:33,040 --> 01:20:36,589
There's one thing I want you
to do for me. Come here.

1058
01:20:37,640 --> 01:20:40,438
- What?
- Win.

1059
01:20:42,760 --> 01:20:46,912
- Win.
- What are we waitin' for? Take us!

1060
01:21:22,400 --> 01:21:24,755
Faster! Faster!

1061
01:21:26,480 --> 01:21:29,552
<i>(Mickey)</i> Keep movin'!
Keep movin'! Faster.

1062
01:21:30,520 --> 01:21:32,875
Pick 'em up! Pick 'em up!

1063
01:21:36,320 --> 01:21:38,550
That's it. That's it.

1064
01:21:40,360 --> 01:21:43,796
- Speed! Speed!
- Come on! Come on!

1065
01:21:46,280 --> 01:21:50,239
- 59!
- One more! Come on, man! Come on!

1066
01:21:50,360 --> 01:21:52,715
44... 45...

1067
01:21:52,840 --> 01:21:55,115
...46... Yeah! 47...

1068
01:21:55,240 --> 01:21:57,629
...48... 49...

1069
01:21:57,760 --> 01:21:59,955
...50!

1070
01:22:19,120 --> 01:22:21,998
Come on! Push! Don't give up!

1071
01:22:22,120 --> 01:22:24,793
Get that olive oil out of ya!

1072
01:22:24,920 --> 01:22:26,751
Push!

1073
01:22:27,680 --> 01:22:30,478
27... 28...

1074
01:22:33,520 --> 01:22:36,478
41... 42... 43...

1075
01:22:37,160 --> 01:22:39,037
26... 27...

1076
01:22:39,160 --> 01:22:41,674
Push! Push! Again!

1077
01:22:44,840 --> 01:22:46,512
Left! Right!

1078
01:22:54,440 --> 01:22:56,351
Yeah!

1079
01:22:56,480 --> 01:22:57,708
That's speed!

1080
01:23:00,720 --> 01:23:02,676
<i>(Mickey)</i> Speed! Speed!

1081
01:23:03,560 --> 01:23:05,516
Speed!

1082
01:23:11,160 --> 01:23:13,116
<i>(music box plays lullaby)</i>

1083
01:23:26,160 --> 01:23:28,116
<i>(whispers)</i> Good night.

1084
01:23:48,160 --> 01:23:50,515
Hey, Rocky!

1085
01:24:25,760 --> 01:24:27,398
Come on. Come on, come on.

1086
01:25:55,040 --> 01:25:57,952
<i>(chanting)</i> Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!

1087
01:26:47,280 --> 01:26:49,919
Good evening.
This is Bill Baldwin speaking to you...

1088
01:26:50,040 --> 01:26:53,589
...from the Spectrum in Philadelphia,
the site of Superfight II...

1089
01:26:53,720 --> 01:26:57,872
...with Rocky Balboa, the challenger,
and Apollo Creed, the world champion.

1090
01:26:58,000 --> 01:27:01,037
My sidekick and partner again tonight -
Stu Nahan.

1091
01:27:01,160 --> 01:27:03,628
For those watching tonight's telecast...

1092
01:27:03,760 --> 01:27:07,548
...we think you're gonna see a real
great battle in every sense of the word.

1093
01:27:11,400 --> 01:27:14,119
Don't worry about nothin'.

1094
01:27:14,240 --> 01:27:16,196
It's OK.

1095
01:27:18,840 --> 01:27:20,796
I gotta go.

1096
01:27:23,280 --> 01:27:27,034
Adrian, I wish the doctor'd
let you go to this fight.

1097
01:27:27,160 --> 01:27:29,435
Me too.

1098
01:27:29,560 --> 01:27:33,314
You're the man. You're number one.
The champ. The best of all time.

1099
01:27:33,440 --> 01:27:36,955
The girls love ya. Men, old people love ya.
Young people love ya.

1100
01:27:37,080 --> 01:27:41,119
You're the best. You're the man.
And he's yours. He's yours. He's yours.

1101
01:27:41,240 --> 01:27:43,390
This bum shouldn't even be
in the same ring.

1102
01:27:43,520 --> 01:27:47,718
I want you to show him
who you are tonight. Stick him.

1103
01:27:48,320 --> 01:27:50,470
<i>(cheering)</i>

1104
01:27:58,720 --> 01:28:01,996
- You help with the baby, right?
- I'll take care of everythin'.

1105
01:28:02,120 --> 01:28:06,591
- OK, cos you're in charge.
- You're gonna be late for your own fight.

1106
01:28:06,720 --> 01:28:10,952
- Everything's gonna be fine.
- Maybe I'd better go fight now.

1107
01:28:11,080 --> 01:28:13,310
- I love you.
- I love you too.

1108
01:28:14,240 --> 01:28:16,674
- Punch his lungs out.
- Adrian, I wish you could go.

1109
01:28:16,800 --> 01:28:18,995
<i>(Paulie)</i> The doctor said no.

1110
01:28:19,520 --> 01:28:21,476
- Take care.
- Good luck.

1111
01:28:21,600 --> 01:28:23,556
<i>(cheering)</i>

1112
01:28:31,960 --> 01:28:36,158
<i>(chanting)</i> Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!

1113
01:28:36,600 --> 01:28:39,353
The champion has let it be known
to the press and radio...

1114
01:28:39,480 --> 01:28:41,914
...that he is in the best shape of his career.

1115
01:28:46,040 --> 01:28:48,349
And Rocky Balboa,
I know, is a 5-1 underdog.

1116
01:28:48,480 --> 01:28:50,755
He's a street brawler from Philadelphia.

1117
01:28:51,040 --> 01:28:54,112
But can he repeat that incredible
performance of ten months ago?

1118
01:28:54,240 --> 01:28:58,028
And, you know, he took a real beating
at the hands of the champion.

1119
01:28:58,400 --> 01:29:00,277
<i>(car horn beeps)</i>

1120
01:29:00,400 --> 01:29:02,914
<i>(Rocky)</i> Carmine!

1121
01:29:03,040 --> 01:29:06,430
Hey, yo, Father Carmine! Father Carmine!

1122
01:29:06,560 --> 01:29:11,190
Hey, Father Carmine, are you home?
Father Carmine! Hey, yo, Father Carmine!

1123
01:29:11,320 --> 01:29:14,630
<i>- Chi e?</i>
- It's me, Rocky Balboa.

1124
01:29:14,760 --> 01:29:19,356
Rocky. <i>Ma che cosa fai la?</i>
<i>Non devi fare la lotta questa sera?</i>

1125
01:29:19,480 --> 01:29:23,678
I'm goin' to the fight, but I was wonderin'
if you could do me a small favour.

1126
01:29:24,000 --> 01:29:26,798
<i>- Ma sicuro. Che favore? Che?</i>
- It's about the fight.

1127
01:29:26,920 --> 01:29:28,990
Now I got the family and the baby.

1128
01:29:29,120 --> 01:29:34,274
I was wonderin' if you could throw down
a blessin', so if I get beat up tonight...

1129
01:29:34,400 --> 01:29:37,073
...it won't be too bad.
Could you do somethin' like that?

1130
01:29:37,200 --> 01:29:40,829
<i>Padre, figlio, spirito santo. E cosi sia.</i>

1131
01:29:43,080 --> 01:29:48,279
Thanks a lot, Father. I gotta go.
I'm so late. See you in church. Take care.

1132
01:30:07,040 --> 01:30:09,110
- Hey, Rock.
- Good luck, son.

1133
01:30:09,240 --> 01:30:11,276
- Yo, Mick!
- Run, or I'll break your head!

1134
01:30:11,560 --> 01:30:13,551
Where ya been? Ya lost your brain?

1135
01:30:13,680 --> 01:30:16,353
- We got a fight, remember that?
- I'm sorry. I'm here.

1136
01:30:16,480 --> 01:30:18,675
Get dressed, will ya?

1137
01:30:19,240 --> 01:30:21,117
<i>Stu, there are many rumours</i>
<i>about this fight.</i>

1138
01:30:21,240 --> 01:30:26,109
<i>The most obvious is a desire for Apollo</i>
<i>to draw first blood, to end it quickly.</i>

1139
01:30:26,680 --> 01:30:28,910
This would prove that
the last fight was a fluke.

1140
01:30:29,480 --> 01:30:31,311
Come on, lightning, thunder!

1141
01:30:31,440 --> 01:30:33,396
Hurricane! Hurricane!

1142
01:30:39,320 --> 01:30:41,038
- Get him.
- I'm gonna get him.

1143
01:30:41,160 --> 01:30:43,879
- Gonna get him.
- He's ours. He's ours!

1144
01:30:47,840 --> 01:30:49,796
It's time, kid.

1145
01:30:57,120 --> 01:30:58,712
OK, let's do it.

1146
01:30:59,600 --> 01:31:01,238
All right, I'm ready.

1147
01:31:07,160 --> 01:31:11,676
- I think I'm startin' to get a headache.
- No, you are in perfect workin' condition.

1148
01:31:11,800 --> 01:31:13,916
- You are perfect.
- You look good, too.

1149
01:31:14,040 --> 01:31:16,031
And you look perfect.

1150
01:31:16,160 --> 01:31:17,639
- Hey, Mick.
- Yeah.

1151
01:31:17,760 --> 01:31:22,151
In case I don't get a chance, I just wanna
say I'm gonna be tryin' hard for you.

1152
01:31:22,280 --> 01:31:25,590
- Thank you.
- Ain't this robe nice?

1153
01:31:25,720 --> 01:31:28,359
It's better than last year.
Remember that baggy one?

1154
01:31:28,480 --> 01:31:33,190
- This is gorgeous. It's perfect.
- Yeah, it's real cute. I like it.

1155
01:31:34,680 --> 01:31:36,716
<i>(cheering and screaming)</i>

1156
01:31:37,880 --> 01:31:40,713
<i>(commentator)</i> Rocky Balboa
heading toward the ring.

1157
01:31:40,840 --> 01:31:44,515
Yes, sir. Rocky Balboa,
known to millions as the Italian Stallion.

1158
01:31:44,640 --> 01:31:48,110
Making his way to the ring.
Why this fighter of limited ability...

1159
01:31:48,240 --> 01:31:50,913
...has gained such popularity
is such a mystery.

1160
01:31:51,360 --> 01:31:56,115
Rocky Balboa. The folks at the Spectrum
are beginning to chant his name.

1161
01:31:56,240 --> 01:32:01,030
- He has an awful lot of backers here.
- Balboa is wearing a black and gold robe.

1162
01:32:01,160 --> 01:32:04,675
He wore a red one the last time
from that meat-packing plant.

1163
01:32:04,800 --> 01:32:07,519
Or from the high school
he never graduated from!

1164
01:32:07,640 --> 01:32:11,758
31 years of age. There he is shaking
hands with the referee, Lou Filippo.

1165
01:32:11,880 --> 01:32:14,952
And we're waiting now for
the champion to come into the ring.

1166
01:32:15,080 --> 01:32:17,150
<i>(chanting)</i> Rocky! Rocky!

1167
01:32:19,720 --> 01:32:21,915
It's certainly packed with Rocky's people.

1168
01:32:22,040 --> 01:32:24,474
I've never seen so many
Italians in one place!

1169
01:32:24,600 --> 01:32:27,319
Hey, hey. You said that. I didn't say that.

1170
01:32:27,440 --> 01:32:29,556
- These people are for you!
- I appreciate it.

1171
01:32:29,680 --> 01:32:31,875
- Are you ready in here?
- I think so.

1172
01:32:32,000 --> 01:32:33,399
Tonight's our night.

1173
01:32:33,520 --> 01:32:37,559
By the sound of the crowd, the champion
is just now coming into the Spectrum.

1174
01:32:37,680 --> 01:32:39,716
And the champion, Apollo Creed.

1175
01:32:39,840 --> 01:32:43,753
And he looks a little more determined
this time than he did the last time.

1176
01:32:44,120 --> 01:32:46,156
- It's Apollo.
- Who'd you expect?

1177
01:32:46,280 --> 01:32:48,191
- I was hopin' he wouldn't show.
- Ha!

1178
01:32:52,080 --> 01:32:53,718
<i>(trainer)</i> The champ of all time!

1179
01:32:53,840 --> 01:32:56,434
Now the champion is
climbing into the ring.

1180
01:32:56,560 --> 01:33:00,155
Very determined-looking.
Very serious right now.

1181
01:33:00,280 --> 01:33:02,191
<i>Rocky doesn't look too confident.</i>

1182
01:33:02,320 --> 01:33:07,553
<i>(trainer)</i> Apollo Creed:
The master of disaster, the best of all time!

1183
01:33:10,960 --> 01:33:14,509
You're goin' down, man.
You're goin' down.

1184
01:33:14,640 --> 01:33:16,790
Don't let it bother ya, kid.

1185
01:33:16,920 --> 01:33:18,956
- Would it bother you?
- Yeah.

1186
01:33:19,080 --> 01:33:24,916
Good evening, ladies and gentlemen!
Welcome to the Philadelphia Spectrum!

1187
01:33:25,040 --> 01:33:26,712
<i>(cheering)</i>

1188
01:33:26,920 --> 01:33:29,992
This is your main event of the evening:

1189
01:33:30,120 --> 01:33:34,511
15 rounds for the heavyweight
championship of the world!

1190
01:33:34,640 --> 01:33:37,154
<i>(cheering)</i>

1191
01:33:38,880 --> 01:33:45,353
In the black corner,
the challenger, weighing 202 pounds...

1192
01:33:45,600 --> 01:33:49,115
...from the great fighting city
of Philadelphia.

1193
01:33:49,240 --> 01:33:51,310
The Italian Stallion...

1194
01:33:51,440 --> 01:33:54,750
...Rocky Balboa!

1195
01:33:54,880 --> 01:33:57,633
<i>(cheering)</i>

1196
01:34:05,680 --> 01:34:10,356
And in the red corner,
weighing 220 pounds...

1197
01:34:10,760 --> 01:34:15,914
...a champion who needs no introduction
anywhere in the civilised world...

1198
01:34:16,040 --> 01:34:18,952
...the true master of disaster...

1199
01:34:19,080 --> 01:34:23,119
...the undefeated heavyweight
champion of the world...

1200
01:34:23,240 --> 01:34:25,595
...the one, the only...

1201
01:34:25,720 --> 01:34:29,269
...Apollo Creed!

1202
01:34:29,400 --> 01:34:31,755
<i>(cheering)</i>

1203
01:34:33,880 --> 01:34:37,429
Referee Lou Filippo
will give the instructions.

1204
01:34:46,800 --> 01:34:51,316
OK, I'm gonna give you the instructions
now, and I expect you to follow 'em.

1205
01:34:51,440 --> 01:34:55,877
Watch your low punches and your kidney
punches. Watch your rabbit punches.

1206
01:34:56,000 --> 01:34:58,150
In case of a knockdown,
you go to the corner...

1207
01:34:58,280 --> 01:35:00,669
...and stay there until
I tell you to come out.

1208
01:35:00,800 --> 01:35:03,234
OK, boys. Let's have a good fight.

1209
01:35:05,040 --> 01:35:07,270
You're goin' down.

1210
01:35:09,880 --> 01:35:11,711
Good luck to you.

1211
01:35:13,120 --> 01:35:15,918
- He's still upset.
- Who cares? Protect that eye.

1212
01:35:16,040 --> 01:35:20,511
No matter what happens, don't go back
to fightin' southpaw till I tell ya. Get him.

1213
01:35:20,640 --> 01:35:23,438
- <i>(attendant)</i> Good luck.
- He'll try to kill you quick.

1214
01:35:23,560 --> 01:35:28,998
If you get through this first round,
then he's ours. Show him who you are.

1215
01:35:29,120 --> 01:35:31,076
<i>(buzzer)</i>

1216
01:35:34,200 --> 01:35:37,556
Rocky Balboa prays in his corner.
The champion dancing over in his.

1217
01:35:37,680 --> 01:35:41,070
We're just seconds away from the fight
of the century: Superfight II.

1218
01:35:41,200 --> 01:35:43,509
And there's the bell.

1219
01:35:43,640 --> 01:35:47,315
The champion comes over in a hurry
and throws a couple of rights and lefts.

1220
01:35:47,440 --> 01:35:52,912
He starts to take command early here.
Moves his feet along the side of the ring.

1221
01:35:53,040 --> 01:35:56,715
Rocky's holding that right hand.
He's fighting right-handed!

1222
01:35:56,840 --> 01:36:00,674
The southpaw from Philly
is fighting right-handed!

1223
01:36:16,080 --> 01:36:19,595
Break that damn jab! Protect that eye!

1224
01:36:22,360 --> 01:36:25,830
- <i>(Apollo)</i> Is that all you got?
- <i>(referee)</i> Break it up there.

1225
01:36:27,720 --> 01:36:29,039
You ready to lay down?

1226
01:36:29,160 --> 01:36:32,675
A good right hand, another
and another thrown by the champion.

1227
01:36:32,800 --> 01:36:35,234
Three good right hands at Balboa.

1228
01:36:36,960 --> 01:36:39,349
And Balboa coming back out.

1229
01:36:39,480 --> 01:36:42,233
A left and a right to the head.

1230
01:36:42,360 --> 01:36:46,672
Balboa appears to be getting hit often, but
he seems to be in pretty good condition.

1231
01:36:46,800 --> 01:36:49,633
A hard right hand thrown
by the champion. Another right.

1232
01:36:49,760 --> 01:36:51,432
Balboa is in trouble now.

1233
01:36:51,640 --> 01:36:55,679
Taking rights and lefts
as the champion begins to open up.

1234
01:36:55,800 --> 01:36:58,837
- It was a tremendous right hand.
- Balboa is down!

1235
01:37:01,680 --> 01:37:02,795
Get back.

1236
01:37:02,920 --> 01:37:06,754
We see Apollo hit that bad left eye
from the first fight.

1237
01:37:06,880 --> 01:37:09,713
The eye that was cut the last time.
Balboa getting up.

1238
01:37:09,840 --> 01:37:13,196
- Go get him, Rocky!
- Go after him, kid! Go after him!

1239
01:37:13,320 --> 01:37:14,469
Yeah.

1240
01:37:15,640 --> 01:37:18,996
And the champion starts to move in again.
Going right, left.

1241
01:37:19,120 --> 01:37:23,750
He's taking those punches pretty well.
And now Balboa is coming right back!

1242
01:37:23,880 --> 01:37:27,156
Right out of the ring. Coming out now.

1243
01:37:27,280 --> 01:37:30,590
Balboa's tagged. Left and right
combinations by the champion.

1244
01:37:30,720 --> 01:37:32,790
- Another left.
<i>- (bell)</i>

1245
01:37:32,920 --> 01:37:36,117
- There's the bell!
- There's the end of the round.

1246
01:37:38,520 --> 01:37:41,671
There's a lot of bad blood
between these two.

1247
01:37:41,800 --> 01:37:43,392
Good round. Good round.

1248
01:37:43,520 --> 01:37:46,512
I can't believe it. He broke my nose again.

1249
01:37:46,640 --> 01:37:50,155
Balboa has gotta be in great shape
to withstand that butchery.

1250
01:37:50,280 --> 01:37:53,272
That's just what it is.
It's plain old butchery.

1251
01:37:53,400 --> 01:37:56,039
Did the switchin' bother you?
You shoulda had him.

1252
01:37:56,160 --> 01:37:59,948
You can't be hurt. You follow?
You can't be hurt, cos you are too tough.

1253
01:38:00,080 --> 01:38:02,150
Don't let up on him.
This man is dangerous.

1254
01:38:02,280 --> 01:38:04,157
Dangerous? <i>I'm</i> dangerous.

1255
01:38:05,360 --> 01:38:08,079
- That guy is crazy.
- No. Listen, he's only a man.

1256
01:38:08,200 --> 01:38:11,112
You can beat him, because you're a tank.

1257
01:38:11,240 --> 01:38:14,437
You're a greasy, fast,
200-pound Italian tank.

1258
01:38:14,560 --> 01:38:18,758
- Go through him! Run over him!
- I'm a tank. I'm gonna get him.

1259
01:38:19,400 --> 01:38:22,790
- This is it, man!
- <i>(commentator)</i> Here we go. Round two.

1260
01:38:23,680 --> 01:38:27,798
Round two. The champion comes back
out. Starting with a left and left and left.

1261
01:38:28,280 --> 01:38:31,750
Left to the chin, left to the head.
Coming around now.

1262
01:38:31,880 --> 01:38:35,714
He's got that right hand cocked.
He's waiting for that precise moment...

1263
01:38:35,840 --> 01:38:39,037
There it is! But here comes Balboa!

1264
01:38:41,680 --> 01:38:43,830
You can't hurt me.
He can't hurt me! No way!

1265
01:38:43,960 --> 01:38:45,916
Break it up. Break it up.

1266
01:38:47,880 --> 01:38:49,836
Break it up. Break clean.

1267
01:38:50,840 --> 01:38:54,515
<i>(Apollo)</i> You're too slow!
Man, you're too slow!

1268
01:38:54,640 --> 01:38:58,918
Get your cameras ready. Watch this.
Watch this. He's goin' down.

1269
01:39:00,640 --> 01:39:02,596
Here it comes!

1270
01:39:10,280 --> 01:39:11,269
Rocky!

1271
01:39:11,400 --> 01:39:12,833
Get up, Rock! Get up!

1272
01:39:13,520 --> 01:39:17,399
Balboa for the second time is down.
Struggling to get up.

1273
01:39:17,520 --> 01:39:21,035
Don't get up. Just stay down there.
Just stay down there, chump!

1274
01:39:21,160 --> 01:39:23,469
- I told you!
- Beautiful! Beautiful!

1275
01:39:26,160 --> 01:39:31,439
Protect that eye, kid! Get at it! The body,
the body, the body! You're a tank, kid!

1276
01:39:31,800 --> 01:39:33,756
I told you! I told you!

1277
01:39:36,160 --> 01:39:38,799
And here comes the champion.

1278
01:39:39,280 --> 01:39:42,795
Here it is. A left and a right
and he's got him back in the corner!

1279
01:39:42,920 --> 01:39:45,832
But here comes Balboa again!
Where does he get that stamina?

1280
01:39:45,960 --> 01:39:48,155
He's got the champion
trapped in the corner.

1281
01:39:48,280 --> 01:39:50,555
And he's breaking left and right.

1282
01:39:50,680 --> 01:39:52,636
<i>(chanting)</i> Rocky! Rocky!

1283
01:40:03,840 --> 01:40:06,195
Keep it up! Keep it up!

1284
01:40:09,720 --> 01:40:13,349
- I'm standing here.
- <i>(commentator)</i> A great second round.

1285
01:40:13,480 --> 01:40:16,631
The round is over,
but they're taunting each other.

1286
01:40:17,000 --> 01:40:21,278
Everybody in the audience
better get ready for World War III.

1287
01:40:22,480 --> 01:40:24,835
I ain't goin' down no more.

1288
01:40:24,960 --> 01:40:27,315
Attaboy! Go get him!

1289
01:40:30,560 --> 01:40:32,596
<i>(bell)</i>

1290
01:40:39,480 --> 01:40:41,436
Come on, kid!

1291
01:40:47,600 --> 01:40:52,196
The champion again with a combination
of lefts and rights to the head.

1292
01:40:53,760 --> 01:40:58,311
- That was another round for Creed.
- Creed keeps piling up the points, but...

1293
01:41:05,400 --> 01:41:06,799
Get him!

1294
01:41:06,920 --> 01:41:08,876
Hit him! Just hit him!

1295
01:41:13,080 --> 01:41:15,548
Another round for Apollo Creed.

1296
01:41:24,880 --> 01:41:29,556
Here comes Balboa again. Lefts and
rights to the midsection. And those hurt.

1297
01:41:34,920 --> 01:41:37,150
<i>(Mickey)</i> Pound the body!

1298
01:41:37,400 --> 01:41:41,996
He's won another round.
He now begins to taunt Balboa again.

1299
01:42:01,000 --> 01:42:02,956
Get out!

1300
01:42:08,160 --> 01:42:09,832
<i>(bell)</i>

1301
01:42:10,280 --> 01:42:15,195
- I'm gonna give that round to Balboa.
- You wonder what's on Creed's mind.

1302
01:42:15,320 --> 01:42:17,390
He's lost his first round.

1303
01:42:23,160 --> 01:42:25,116
Go for it, Rock!

1304
01:42:32,640 --> 01:42:35,154
Balboa is on his way.

1305
01:42:40,080 --> 01:42:42,799
Hands up! Hands up!
Now, just stick and move!

1306
01:42:42,920 --> 01:42:45,832
This man is breakin' you up inside!
Now, stick and move!

1307
01:42:45,960 --> 01:42:47,552
<i>(bell)</i>

1308
01:42:47,680 --> 01:42:49,830
Lightning! Thunder!

1309
01:43:06,800 --> 01:43:09,394
Hit him back!

1310
01:43:11,760 --> 01:43:15,958
I thought he took a beating ten months
ago, Stu, but tonight it's twice as bad!

1311
01:43:17,600 --> 01:43:21,149
Another round for
the champion, Apollo Creed.

1312
01:43:22,840 --> 01:43:25,877
The left eye is closed.
Now bust him, understand?

1313
01:43:28,000 --> 01:43:31,754
- Stay away from him.
- Don't let him breathe! Get him!

1314
01:43:33,280 --> 01:43:35,236
<i>(bell)</i>

1315
01:43:46,920 --> 01:43:51,516
Balboa's taking another beating
in the corner.

1316
01:43:51,640 --> 01:43:53,995
Another round for the champion.

1317
01:44:10,360 --> 01:44:12,316
<i>(bell)</i>

1318
01:44:30,360 --> 01:44:32,510
You got him beat on points.
You understand?

1319
01:44:32,640 --> 01:44:34,915
Stick and move!
Don't go for the knockout!

1320
01:44:35,040 --> 01:44:37,759
- He's gonna fall.
- He's breakin' you up inside!

1321
01:44:37,880 --> 01:44:39,950
- How's that eye now?
- It works.

1322
01:44:40,080 --> 01:44:43,072
- You can't do much more with that.
- I know what I'm doin'.

1323
01:44:43,200 --> 01:44:46,510
- You get in trouble one more time...
- Please don't stop nothin'!

1324
01:44:46,640 --> 01:44:48,392
Now, listen, let me stop it.

1325
01:44:48,520 --> 01:44:50,750
- You're gettin' killed!
- It's my life.

1326
01:44:50,880 --> 01:44:55,192
Apollo ahead. All he has to do
is stay away and he retains the title.

1327
01:44:55,320 --> 01:44:59,199
- Just stick and move.
- It ain't gonna be like last time.

1328
01:44:59,320 --> 01:45:02,710
- Switch now to southpaw anyway.
- No tricks. I ain't switchin'.

1329
01:45:02,840 --> 01:45:05,957
- Yeah, but you're fadin' out.
- I don't need no tricks.

1330
01:45:06,080 --> 01:45:08,799
- I ain't switchin'.
- You gotta plan. You gotta switch.

1331
01:45:08,920 --> 01:45:10,672
He's ready. Believe me.

1332
01:45:10,800 --> 01:45:12,995
Don't go for the knockout.
You got him burned!

1333
01:45:13,120 --> 01:45:16,556
They come to the centre of the ring
for the fifteenth and final round.

1334
01:45:16,840 --> 01:45:19,991
- You're goin' down.
- No. No way.

1335
01:45:20,120 --> 01:45:22,759
Here we go.
Let's see what Creed does here now.

1336
01:45:22,880 --> 01:45:26,236
Creed has started to move in on Balboa.
He's going for the knockout.

1337
01:45:26,360 --> 01:45:29,716
The champion comes out
jabbing with that left hand.

1338
01:45:29,840 --> 01:45:32,638
- The champion is beating Balboa.
- Now! Now!

1339
01:45:36,840 --> 01:45:39,195
Balboa just nearly floored the champ!

1340
01:45:39,320 --> 01:45:41,754
A hook caught
the exhausted champ off guard!

1341
01:45:41,880 --> 01:45:44,758
Creed doesn't know where he is!
It's blind instinct.

1342
01:45:44,880 --> 01:45:50,273
Balboa is staggering from exhaustion -
but a right to the head of the champion.

1343
01:45:50,400 --> 01:45:53,073
Another right, and a left.
He's got him into the corner.

1344
01:45:53,200 --> 01:45:55,555
Stay away from him!

1345
01:45:55,680 --> 01:45:59,958
He's got this thing won if he stays away,
but now it is Creed coming back.

1346
01:46:00,080 --> 01:46:02,913
- Creed with a left hand.
- Go for it!

1347
01:46:03,760 --> 01:46:07,309
What's keepin' these two guys up?
A tremendous moment.

1348
01:46:07,440 --> 01:46:09,396
Now!

1349
01:46:10,800 --> 01:46:14,873
Here comes Balboa,
but the champion back with another left.

1350
01:46:17,440 --> 01:46:19,396
Get away from him!

1351
01:46:20,400 --> 01:46:24,791
A right hand! A right hand! It's Creed!
Now it's Balboa! Now it's Creed!

1352
01:46:24,920 --> 01:46:29,118
What a tremendous fight!
They're standing toe to toe.

1353
01:46:29,240 --> 01:46:33,153
I don't know why the champion
is fighting Balboa's fight.

1354
01:46:37,240 --> 01:46:39,196
Go, Rocky! Go for it!

1355
01:46:40,880 --> 01:46:42,836
A tremendous left to the head.

1356
01:46:42,960 --> 01:46:44,916
A left.

1357
01:46:45,320 --> 01:46:47,276
A left.

1358
01:46:59,520 --> 01:47:01,476
One!

1359
01:47:05,360 --> 01:47:07,828
Two!

1360
01:47:09,160 --> 01:47:10,832
Creed will retain the title!

1361
01:47:10,960 --> 01:47:16,717
If neither gets up, it's a draw,
and Creed will win the title automatically!

1362
01:47:16,960 --> 01:47:18,996
- Four!
- Get up, man!

1363
01:47:19,960 --> 01:47:22,554
Get on your feet!

1364
01:47:22,800 --> 01:47:24,518
Five!

1365
01:47:24,640 --> 01:47:27,234
- Balboa reaches for another!
- Get up, Rock!

1366
01:47:28,920 --> 01:47:30,990
Six!

1367
01:47:32,240 --> 01:47:34,913
- Now the champ is trying to get up!
- Seven!

1368
01:47:35,040 --> 01:47:37,998
Get up, Rocky!

1369
01:47:40,280 --> 01:47:42,714
Eight!

1370
01:47:45,840 --> 01:47:47,751
Nine!

1371
01:47:47,880 --> 01:47:50,155
The champ is going. And he's down!

1372
01:47:50,280 --> 01:47:52,236
Ten!

1373
01:47:57,480 --> 01:48:00,517
He made it!
Rocky Balboa has shocked the world!

1374
01:48:00,640 --> 01:48:03,632
He is the new heavyweight
champion of the world!

1375
01:48:04,800 --> 01:48:06,916
Ladies and gentlemen...

1376
01:48:07,040 --> 01:48:12,114
...in a stunning upset,
scoring a win by knockout...

1377
01:48:12,240 --> 01:48:15,391
...the new heavyweight
champion of the world...

1378
01:48:17,320 --> 01:48:18,389
Yo, Creed.

1379
01:48:22,040 --> 01:48:23,951
Good luck.

1380
01:48:24,720 --> 01:48:27,678
Excuse me. Excuse me.

1381
01:48:27,800 --> 01:48:30,997
I can't believe this is happenin'. I can't...

1382
01:48:32,600 --> 01:48:36,593
And I just wanna say thanks to Apollo.
For fightin' me, Apollo.

1383
01:48:37,760 --> 01:48:41,036
I wanna thank...
thank Mickey for trainin' me.

1384
01:48:42,360 --> 01:48:45,716
- <i>(man)</i> We love you, Rock!
- Yeah, and I love youse, too.

1385
01:48:45,840 --> 01:48:47,717
<i>(cheering)</i>

1386
01:48:47,840 --> 01:48:50,195
Most of all I wanna thank God.

1387
01:48:52,280 --> 01:48:54,635
Except for my kid bein' born...

1388
01:48:56,200 --> 01:48:59,909
...this is the greatest night
in the history of my life.

1389
01:49:01,080 --> 01:49:04,914
I just wanna say one thing...
to my wife who's home.

1390
01:49:07,600 --> 01:49:10,239
Yo, Adrian! I did it!

1391
01:49:10,360 --> 01:49:13,557
I love you. I love you.

